Massachusetts</a>. Bay Path offers both&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Women%27s_college">all-women</a>&nbsp;Bachelor&#39;s degree programs (both on-campus and online), and co-educational master&#39;s degree programs (both on-campus and online). The University also has a One Day A Week College for adult women and the American Women&#39;s College, the first all-women online college.<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bay_Path_University#cite_note-1">[1]</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Founded in 1897 as the Bay Path Institute, the college has gone through several name changes and upgrades to its accreditation status. From 1988 to 2014 it was known as Bay Path College. Bay Path University is a member of the&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cooperating_Colleges_of_Greater_Springfield">Cooperating Colleges of Greater Springfield</a>, an eight-college consortium.</p>\r\n', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11, 'Bay State College', 1955, 'USA', '', '', ' MA 02116, United States ', '122 Commonwealth Avenue, Boston, MA 02116, United States ', '', 'Completed Filled and Application form\r\nIELTS--- 6.0 Required with no module less than 5.5(IELTS 5.5 for foundation course)/TOEFL IBT---50 or above\r\n10+2----60% or above\r\nPassport Copy\r\nSOP\r\nApplication Fee: Waived for Study Metro Student\r\nBank Statement (One Year Fee+ One year living expenses)\r\n\r\nI20 will be released in 7 Days\r\nIf student is going through foundation course then he will get admission in second year of bachelor degree after foundation course.\r\n\r\nIf student do not want to go for the IELTS/TOEFl or they are not having the sufficient score then the college is having a password test also, if student pass the test(Minimum Score should be 5.5) then they can get admission in degree course.', 'public', '', 'Foundation Courses Bachelor Degree Associate Degree  Bachelor''s Degree Criminal Justice  Criminal Justice: Domestic and International Security Concentration Entertainment Management Entertainment Management - Audio Production Concentration Fashion Merchandising Information Technology Management Management - Finance Concentration Management - Healthcare Management Management - Hospitality Management Concentration Management - Information Systems Management - Marketing Concentration Nursing (RN to BSN)  Associates Degree Accounting  Business Administration Criminal Justice Entertainment Management Entertainment Management - Audio Production Concentration Fashion Design Fashion Retail Merchandising Health Studies Health Studies - Medical Assisting Concentration Hospitality Management  Information Technology Nursing Physical Therapist Assistant Retail Business Management’   Certificate Program is Also Available  Fees for 2014-15  Bachelor Degree Fees per year  Health Studies: $22,470  Accounting/Business Administration/Criminal Justice/Fashion Merchandising/Fashion Design/Entertainment management/Hospitality Management/Management/Information Management/: $24,780  Nursing: $25,740 Nursing (RN to BSN): $16,500 Physical Therapy Assistant: $25,470   For Foundation Course:  $22,000 Per Year  Associate Degree:   Intake :  September, January, May  Note: If student will enroll for September intake, then student will get the $12,000 Scholarship in foundation course.  Scholarship: Bachelor Degree student will be getting the scholarship $12000($3000 Each year)  Application Fee: $100/$25 for Nursing Program  Admission Requirement :  Completed Filled and Application form IELTS--- 6.0 Required with no module less than 5.5(IELTS 5.5 for foundation course)/TOEFL IBT---50 or above 10+2----60% or above Passport Copy SOP Application Fee: Waived for Study Metro Student Bank Statement (One Year Fee+ One year living expenses)  I20 will be released in 7 Days If student is going through foundation course then he will get admission in second year of bachelor degree after foundation course.  If student do not want to go for the IELTS/TOEFl or they are not having the sufficient score then the college is having a password test also, if student pass the test(Minimum Score should be 5.5) then they can get admission in degree course.  Most Important Note: Student can get the 29 months Extended OPT.', '', '', '', '', 'on', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'https://twitter.com/baystatecollege', 'https://twitter.com/baystatecollege ', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/baystatecollege ', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/baystatecollege ', '', '', '[""]', '[" Boston is the largest city in the New England region of the North eastern United States. Other major capitals within easy travelling distance include New York, Philadelphia and Washington DC. Bay State College has built a reputation for offering a unique, high-quality curriculum for the serious student. Due to small classes, individualized attention, and a faculty of industry professionals who bring their experience into the classroom, the school students are successfully able to pursue career-focused studies in today\\u2019s fastest-growing industries.  In commitment to their academic and professional advancement, students are given the opportunity to intern at some of the best companies in the nation."]', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Boston is the largest city in the New England region of the North eastern United States. Other major capitals within easy travelling distance include New York, Philadelphia and Washington DC.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bay State College has built a reputation for offering a unique, high-quality curriculum for the serious student. Due to small classes, individualized attention, and a faculty of industry professionals who bring their experience into the classroom, the school students are successfully able to pursue career-focused studies in today&rsquo;s fastest-growing industries.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In commitment to their academic and professional advancement, students are given the opportunity to intern at some of the best companies in the nation.</p>\r\n', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(12, 'Bristol University', 1991, 'USA', '', '', 'Anaheim, California', '2390 E Orangewood Ave, Anaheim, CA 92806, United States', '', 'Please submit all required documents to  international_admission@bristoluniversity.edu  or send to us by mail at the \r\nbelow address:\r\nBristol University\r\nInternational Office\r\n2390 E. Orangewood Ave, #485\r\nAnaheim, CA 92867\r\nStep 1:\r\nComplete the Admission Application online or obtained a soft copy of the application by contact us directly  at international_admission@bristoluniversity.edu.\r\nPay $50 Application Fee. Students may pay in person or by phone.\r\nFill in the I-20 Application which can be downloaded at I-20-Application and submit to the school by emailing/faxing/mailing.\r\nSubmit Certified English translation OR Notarized Translation of your degree (high school degree for Bachelor program, Bachelor degree for Master program).\r\nSubmit Certified English translation OR Notarized Translation transcript along with your OFFICIAL transcript.\r\nSubmit English proof: TOEFL / IELTS score. The expected entry level is equivalent to 450 TOEFL PBT for Bachelor or 500 TOEFL PBT for Master degree. \r\nSubmit Copy of Passport: of the student and any dependents traveling with him/her.\r\nSubmit Copy of financial statement: Must be within 3 months of issuing. It could be a bank statement or a letter of account confirmation from the bank. Must have at least $12,000 on account for the student him/herself plus $4,000 for each extra dependent. Fill out form Affidavit of Support if someone else is sponsoring the student and have the form notarized.\r\n Step 2:\r\nAfter the admission requirements are met, you will receive an Acceptance Letter and the school will send the Enrollment Agreement for you to sign\r\nSign the enrollment agreement\r\nPay I-20 processing fee of $100 (non-refundable). \r\nStep 3:\r\nThe University will issue an I-20. Make sure every information on your I-20 is correct. If there is a mistake, please call or email us IMMEDIATELY to resolve the matter and prevent any delay. It can usually take up to 7 business days for I-20 to be processed and another possibly 5 days to ship to whichever country the student is in.\r\n\r\n\r\nTuition and Fees\r\nApplicable for all students (as of January 2016)\r\nDegree Programs\r\nProgram\r\nCredit Units\r\nTuition\r\nper unit\r\nTuition\r\nper course\r\nTotal Tuition fee\r\nAssociate of Science in Business Administration (ASBA)\r\n60\r\n$395\r\n$1,185\r\n$23,700\r\nBachelor of Science in Business Administration (BSBA)\r\n120\r\n$395\r\n$1,185\r\n$47,400\r\nMasters of Business Administration (MBA)\r\n39**\r\n$595\r\n$1,785\r\n$23,205\r\n *Tuition includes on-line library fee.\r\n', 'private', '', 'Associate Degree in Business Administration ? Bachelor Degree in Business Administration ?', '', '22780', '', '', 'on', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.facebook.com/BristolUniversityAnaheim ', 'https://twitter.com/bristoluniversi ', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCWxNF3I_fg0N6h0HBONN1Lw', 'https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCWxNF3I_fg0N6h0HBONN1Lw', '', '', '[""]', '["On March 18, 2016, the Accrediting Council for Independent Colleges and Schools denied Bristol University\\u2019s application for renewal of its accreditation. On March 21, 2016, Bristol University filed a lawsuit against ACICS challenging the denial. On March 22, 2016, the Court ordered ACICS to reinstate Bristol University\\u2019s accreditation pending further litigation. Bristol University\\u2019s accreditation renewal is currently in question."]', '<p>On March 18, 2016, the Accrediting Council for Independent Colleges and Schools denied Bristol University&rsquo;s application for renewal of its accreditation. On March 21, 2016, Bristol University filed a lawsuit against ACICS challenging the denial. On March 22, 2016, the Court ordered ACICS to reinstate Bristol University&rsquo;s accreditation pending further litigation. Bristol University&rsquo;s accreditation renewal is currently in question.</p>\r\n', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(13, 'California Baptist University ', 1950, 'USA', '', '', 'Riverside, California, United States', 'Riverside, California, United States', 'CBU is accredited by the Western Association of Schools and Colleges.', '', 'private', '', '', 'Ronald L. Ellis, PhD', '', '', '', 'on', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.facebook.com/CalBaptist/ ', 'https://twitter.com/calbaptist/ ', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/cbuTVnow ', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/cbuTVnow ', '', '', '[""]', '["California Baptist University (Cal Baptist or CBU) is a private, Christian, liberal arts university located in Riverside, California, United States. Originally founded in 1950 as California Baptist College, it is controlled by the California Southern Baptist Convention, an organization affiliated with the Southern Baptist Convention. CBU is accredited by the Western Association of Schools and Colleges."]', '<p>California Baptist University (Cal Baptist or CBU) is a private, Christian, liberal arts university located in Riverside, California, United States. Originally founded in 1950 as California Baptist College, it is controlled by the California Southern Baptist Convention, an organization affiliated with the Southern Baptist Convention. CBU is accredited by the Western Association of Schools and Colleges.</p>\r\n', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(14, ' California Institute of Advanced Management', 1973, 'USA', '', '', ' Los Angeles basin in the town of El Monte', ' Los Angeles basin in the town of El Monte,U.S.A', '', ' A Bachelor’s degree in any field from an accredited institution in the U.S. or completion of the equivalent to a U.S. Bachelor’s degree from an recognized/accredited institution overseas with 3.0 or higher GPA (on a 4.0 scale) as shown in the following supporting documents:', 'private', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'on', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.facebook.com/pages/California-Institute-of-Advanced-Management/280808095353171 ', 'https://twitter.com/CIAMMBA ', '', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/california-institute-of-advanced-management-ciam-', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/CIAMMBA  ', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/CIAMMBA  ', '', '', '[""]', '["Located centrally in the Los Angeles basin in the town of El Monte, the California Institute of Advanced Management (CIAM) has achieved national accreditation within a short time after its original licensing. This unique graduate business educational program combines theory and practical experience in a combination that provides students actual consulting projects in each of the twelve courses of the degree program."]', '<p>Located centrally in the Los Angeles basin in the town of El Monte, the California Institute of Advanced Management (CIAM) has achieved national accreditation within a short time after its original licensing. This unique graduate business educational program combines theory and practical experience in a combination that provides students actual consulting projects in each of the twelve courses of the degree program.</p>\r\n', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
