  Education,  English/Literature,  Environmental Science,  Environmental Studies,  Exercise Science,  Geography,  Geology,  Global Studies,  Health Education,  Health Science,  History,  Mathematics,  Multidisciplinary Studies,  Music,  Music Education,  Nursing,  Philosophy,  Physical Education,  Political Science,  Pre-Law Program,  Psychology,  Social Studies,  Social Work,  Sociology,  Spanish,  Sports Administration, Theater Arts, Women''s and Gender Studies', 'David S. Wolk', '2191', '', '', 'on', '', '', '', '', '', 'www.castleton.edu', 'https://www.facebook.com/castletonedu ', 'https://twitter.com/castletonedu ', '', 'https://www.linkedin.com/edu/school ', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/castletonedu ', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/castletonedu ', '', '', '[""]', '[" Since Castleton first opened its doors in 1787, it has been dedicated to providing a quality level of higher education to those eager to learn.  Today, the University\\u00a0stands on a foundation of over two hundred years of tradition,\\u00a0providing this same high quality liberal arts education.\\u00a0 Castleton is small enough to be a community where individuals matter, yet large enough to offer a diverse and challenging curriculum. Students have the opportunity to expand their knowledge in small class sizes among our highly qualified faculty who are strongly encouraged to develop their teaching skills and research interests.  These ingredients are combined with a diverse composition of local, out-of-state and growing international student population that provide for various and extended learning opportunities for all. Not only does Castleton influence its students, but the students also have the ability and often do impact Castleton.  \\u201cCome to our campus, and you will learn that you too can make a difference in your university\\u00a0as you prepare to make a difference in the world.\\u201d  - President Dave Wolk"]', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Since Castleton first opened its doors in 1787, it has been dedicated to providing a quality level of higher education to those eager to learn. Today, the University&nbsp;stands on a foundation of over two hundred years of tradition,&nbsp;providing this same high quality liberal arts education.&nbsp; Castleton is small enough to be a community where individuals matter, yet large enough to offer a diverse and challenging curriculum. Students have the opportunity to expand their knowledge in small class sizes among our highly qualified faculty who are strongly encouraged to develop their teaching skills and research interests. These ingredients are combined with a diverse composition of local, out-of-state and growing international student population that provide for various and extended learning opportunities for all. Not only does Castleton influence its students, but the students also have the ability and often do impact Castleton.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;Come to our campus, and you will learn that you too can make a difference in your university&nbsp;as you prepare to make a difference in the world.&rdquo; - President Dave Wolk</p>\r\n', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
