nterior Design Design and Merchandising HS Graduate M.S. Plan B Specialization Early Childhood Education Human Development and Family Studies HS Undergraduate B.S. Earth Sciences Geosciences NR Graduate Ph.D. Earth Sciences, Geosciences Geosciences NR Graduate Ph.D. Specialization Earth Sciences, Watershed Science Geosciences NR Graduate Ph.D. Specialization Ecological Restoration Forest and Rangeland Stewardship NR Undergraduate Minor Ecology Ecology UW Graduate M.S. Plan A Ecology Ecology UW Graduate M.S. Plan B Ecology Ecology UW Graduate Ph.D. Ecology, Ecological Risk Assessment and Management Ecology UW Graduate M.S. Specialization Ecology, Ecological Risk Assessment and Management Ecology UW Graduate Ph.D. Specialization', 'Tony Frank', '32236', '', '', 'on', '', '', '', '', '', 'www.colostate.edu', 'https://www.facebook.com/coloradostateuniversity ', 'https://twitter.com/coloradostateu ', '', 'https://www.linkedin.com/home?goback ', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/ColoradoStateUniv ', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/ColoradoStateUniv ', '', '', '[""]', '["Colorado State University (also referred to as Colorado State and CSU) is a public research university located in Fort Collins, in the U.S. state of Colorado. The university is the state''s land grant university, and the flagship university of the Colorado State University System. The current enrollment is approximately 32,236 students, including resident and non-resident instruction students[4] and the University is planning on having 35,000 students by 2020.[5] The university has approximately 1,540 faculty in eight colleges and 55 academic departments. Bachelor''s degrees are offered in 65 fields of study, with master''s degrees in 55 fields. Colorado State confers doctoral degrees in 40 fields of study, in addition to a professional degree in veterinary medicine. In fiscal year 2012, CSU spent $375.9 million on research and development, ranking 60th in the nation overall and 34th when excluding medical school spending."]', '<p>Colorado State University (also referred to as Colorado State and CSU) is a public research university located in Fort Collins, in the U.S. state of Colorado. The university is the state&#39;s land grant university, and the flagship university of the Colorado State University System.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The current enrollment is approximately 32,236 students, including resident and non-resident instruction students[4] and the University is planning on having 35,000 students by 2020.[5] The university has approximately 1,540 faculty in eight colleges and 55 academic departments. Bachelor&#39;s degrees are offered in 65 fields of study, with master&#39;s degrees in 55 fields. Colorado State confers doctoral degrees in 40 fields of study, in addition to a professional degree in veterinary medicine. In fiscal year 2012, CSU spent $375.9 million on research and development, ranking 60th in the nation overall and 34th when excluding medical school spending.</p>\r\n', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(28, 'Concordia University Chicago (CUC)', 1864, 'USA', '', '', 'River Forest, Illinois, United States', 'River Forest, Illinois, United States', '', '', 'public', '', '', 'Rev. Dr. Daniel L. Gard', '5286', '', '', 'on', '', '', '', '', '', 'www.cuchicago.edu', 'https://www.facebook.com/ConcordiaUniversityChicago ', 'https://twitter.com/CUChicago ', '', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/concordia-university-chicago ', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/ConcordiaUChicago ', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/ConcordiaUChicago ', '', '', '[""]', '["A 150 year history as a bricks-and-mortar institution makes Concordia-Chicago a focal point in the local community. Our history of excellence has turned Concordia University Chicago into a byword for the highest standards of teaching. Furthermore, its national and international profile continues to grow, and currently students from 37 US states and 25 countries study the academic programs. \\u00a0 Students can get admission without IELTS\\/TOEFL and get I20 in 10-14 business working days.\\u00a0 MBA Program is available for 1 and 2 years.  \\u00a0 CUC is closely affiliated with Global university Systems (GUS)."]', '<p>A 150 year history as a bricks-and-mortar institution makes Concordia-Chicago a focal point in the local community. Our history of excellence has turned Concordia University Chicago into a byword for the highest standards of teaching. Furthermore, its national and international profile continues to grow, and currently students from 37 US states and 25 countries study the academic programs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Students can get admission without IELTS/TOEFL and get I20 in 10-14 business working days.&nbsp; MBA Program is available for 1 and 2 years.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>CUC is closely affiliated with Global university Systems (GUS).</p>\r\n', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(29, 'Concordia University Location:  St Paul, Minnesota', 1893, 'USA', '', '', 'St. Paul, Minnesota, United States', 'St. Paul, Minnesota, United States', 'Higher Learning Commission - North Central Association\r\nConcordia University is accredited by the Higher Learning Commission and a member of the North Central Association. Concordia University, St. Paul has been accredited since 1967, \r\nNational Council for Accreditation of Teacher Education\r\nAll of Concordia University''s professional teacher education licensure programs have been accredited by the National Council for Accreditation of Teacher Education (NCATE) since 1969. The programs were most recently re-accredited in 2008. Concordia University''s graduate programs in education are also accredited by NCATE.\r\nAccreditation Council for Business Schools and Programs\r\nConcordia University, St. Paul is nationally accredited by the Accreditation Council for Business Schools and Programs to offer the following business degrees: Bachelor of Business Administration with majors in accounting, finance, marketing, a double major in accounting and finance, and a double major in finance and marketing.\r\nMinnesota Board of Teaching\r\nAll teacher licensure programs are approved by the Minnesota Board of Teaching. The most recent approval was completed in 2008.\r\nFederal Title II Reporting for Teacher Education\r\nAs per NCATE and Federal Title II guidelines, Concordia University reports its professional licensure examination pass rates for academic year 2011-2012:\r\nCouncil for Higher Education Administration\r\nConcordia University is a member of the Council for Higher Education Administration (CHEA). A national advocate and institutional voice for self-regulation of academic quality through accreditation, CHEA is an association of 3,000 degree-granting colleges and universities and recognizes 60 institutional and programmatic accrediting organizations.\r\nCourses Offered: \r\nThey Do have good number of Programs, refer the below link for the entire list of Graduate Program and few mention below which are some hot course.\r\nhttp://www.csp.edu/academics/graduate/ \r\n?  Master of Arts in Teaching (MAT) - Initial K-6 Licensure \r\n?  MBA - Cybersecurity \r\n?  MBA - Health Care Management \r\n?  MBA - Master of Business Administration \r\n\r\nRefer the link for Undergraduate Programs.\r\n\r\nhttp://www.csp.edu/academics/undergraduate-majors-minors/ \r\n\r\nEligibility Criteria:\r\nUndergraduate Application Process  \r\nOne who has not attended an institution of higher education for at least one year must submit the following:\r\n1. Online or Paper Application\r\n2. $30 Application Fee\r\n\r\n3. Official High School Transcripts (for all institutions attended) \r\n4. Official Credit Evaluation of credits earned/degrees completed at any non-United States institution\r\n- Evaluations must be from approved members of the National Association of Credential Evaluation Services \r\n5. Proof of English Proficiency (if English is not your first language) or ACT/SAT Score\r\ni. Students from Global Language Institute (GLI) Completion of Mastering Level \r\nii. Students from Atlanta English Institute (AEI) Completion of Level Seven \r\niii. Students from Spring International Language Center (SILC) Completion of Level Six\r\niv. Students from English Language School (ELS) Completion of Level 109 AND IELTS test score of 5.5 or TOEFL iBT 65 or completion of Level 112\r\nv. TOEFL iBT 65 or 513 PBT\r\nvi. IELTS overall band score of 5.5 or higher (International English Language Testing System)\r\n6. Certification of Finances indicating the financial source for the expense of attending Concordia University\r\nGraduate Application Process  \r\nOne who has received a bachelor''s degree and is pursuing a graduate degree must submit the following:\r\n1. Graduate Application \r\n\r\n2. $50 Application Fee\r\n- Pay online or submit check payable to Concordia University\r\n3. Official College Transcript from institution granting bachelor’s degree \r\n4. Official Credit Evaluation of degree(s) earned at any non-United States institution\r\n- Evaluations must be from approved members of the National Association of Credential Evaluation Services \r\n5. Proof of English Proficiency (if English is not your first language)\r\ni. Completion of Level 112 at an English Language School (ELS) or Accelerated Level at Global Language Institute (GLI)\r\nii. Completion of Level 6 at an approved English school\r\niii. TOEFL- iBT score of 78 or TOEFL PBT score of 547\r\niv. An equated score of 80 or better on the Michigan Test\r\nv. IELTS overall band score of 6 or higher (International English Language Testing System) \r\n6. Certification of Finances indicating the financial source for the expense of attending Concordia University. This form will be emailed with acknowledgement of application.\r\n7. Personal Statement \r\nBank Certificate: 40360 USD\r\nTution Fees:\r\nUnder Graduate: $20,750 Per academic Year. \r\nGraduate: Graduate international student tuition is $2207 per credit hour\r\nFees Varies from Subjects refer the below link.\r\nhttp://online.csp.edu/admissions/tuition-and-financial-aid \r\n\r\nIntake: Jan & May & Sept', 'http://www.csp.edu/academics/undergraduate-majors-minors/ ', 'public', '', '', 'Rev. Tom Ries', '2800', '', '', 'on', '', '', '', '', '', 'http://www.csp.edu/ ', 'https://www.facebook.com/concordiauniversitystpaul ', 'https://twitter.com/concordiastpaul ', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/ConcordiaUniversity ', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/ConcordiaUniversity ', '', '', '[""]', '["About Concordia St Paul: Concordia University - St. Paul is registered as a private institution with the Minnesota Office of Higher Education pursuant to sections 136A.61 to 136A.71. Registration is not an endorsement of the institution. Credits earned at the institution may not transfer to all other institutions."]', '<p>About Concordia St Paul:</p>\r\n\r\