ed as one of the West''s best college towns."]', '<p>Humboldt State students enjoy an extraordinary college experience, taking small classes taught by professors who know them by name. They live and learn in one of the world&#39;s most beautiful places&mdash;near ancient redwood forests, mountains and beaches. We are located 275 miles north of San Francisco in the town of Arcata, which is recognized as one of the West&#39;s best college towns.</p>\r\n', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(49, 'Husson University', 1898, 'USA', '', '', '1 College Cir, Bangor, ME 04401, United States\r\nhttp://www.husson.edu.', '1 College Cir, Bangor, ME 04401, United States\r\nhttp://www.husson.edu.', '', 'Apply at www.commonapp.org today!\r\nApplication Deadlines: Spring Semester – November 1;   Fall Semester – June 1\r\nPrograms in Nursing, Physical Therapy, Occupational Therapy and Pharmacy enroll students during Fall Semester only. Deadline for applications for these programs is January 1. \r\n\r\nUndergraduate Admission Requirements\r\nProof of high school completion.\r\nMinimum 2.0 GPA on a scale of 4.0, or its equivalent. \r\nFor specific program GPA requirements, click here. \r\nTOEFL minimum 75; IELTS 6.0 minimum.\r\nUndergraduate Admission Process\r\nStep 1:    Complete the Common Application atwww.commonapp.org\r\nStep 2:    Submit the following documents tointernational@husson.edu \r\n           a.)    High School transcript in English. Transfer students must submit transcripts to an evaluation service holding membership in NACES. www.naces.org\r\n           b.)    Official English language proficiency test score\r\n           c.)    Photocopy of passport ID page\r\n           d.)    Husson Declaration of Finances form (click here) and bank statement. \r\nStep 3: Schedule an appointment for a Skype interview international@husson.edu \r\n\r\nScholarships\r\nEvery undergraduate international applicant is screened for merit based scholarships:\r\nPresidential Global Scholarship ranging between $1,000 and $10,000. \r\nAll scholarships are renewable for all undergraduate years by maintaining a minimum 2.5 GPA and positive campus citizenship.\r\nGraduate Admission :\r\nApplicants should fill out sections 1 through 5 of the graduate application, and include or forward the following supplemental documentation: \r\n? $50 Application Fee \r\n? Statement of Purpose Essay \r\n? Résumé or Curriculum Vitae (optional) \r\n? Immunization Records (If born after December 31, 1956) \r\n? Official graduate admissions test scores sent to Graduate Admissions (Not required for MS-OT programs) \r\n? TOEFL or IELTS Scores (international applicants only) \r\n? Official transcripts from previous undergraduate and graduate work sent to Graduate Admissions (International applicants must submit transcripts from a current NACES member.) \r\n? Letters of Recommendation sent to the Office of Graduate Admissions from the recommender \r\n? Copy of RN License (Nursing applicants only) \r\n? Background check (Pastoral Counseling applicants only) \r\n? Self assessment form (MS-OT applicants only)\r\n\r\nTuition Fee :\r\n\r\nREGULAR DIVISION - Undergraduate Programs Regular Undergraduate Tuition\r\n(typical load of 16 credits fall, 15 credits spring - full-time first year) $535 per credit hour. $16,585 for a full-load (31 credits) – \r\n\r\nMaster of Business Administration (Traditional Classroom and Online) $450 per credit \r\nhour.\r\n Master of Education (Traditional Classroom and Online) $385 per credit hour. \r\nMaster of Science in Clinical Mental Health Counseling $560 per credit hour. \r\nMaster of Science in Criminal Justice Administration $450 per credit hour. \r\nMaster of Science in Human Relations $560 per credit hour.\r\nMaster of Science in Nursing and Post-Master''s Certificates (APPN/FNP/Nursing Education)\r\n$560 per credit hour.\r\nMaster of Science in Occupational Therapy - Professional Phase: Years 3, 4, and 5. (See base tuition for years 1 and 2)$620 per credit hour.\r\nMaster of Science in Pharmacology$560 per credit hour. \r\nMaster of Science in School Counseling $560 per credit hour. – \r\n\r\n\r\n', 'private', '', 'B.S. Accounting/MBA B.S. Accounting B.S. Accounting/Computer Information Systems A.S. Accounting Minor in Accounting School of Business and Management Master of Business Administration (MBA) Concentration options: Biotechnology & Innovation General (Corporate) Healthcare Management Hospitality and Tourism Management Organizational Management Risk Management B.S. Business Administration/Master of Business Administration (MBA) Concentration options for B.S. degree: Entrepreneurship/Small Business Management Financial Management Healthcare Management Interdisciplinary Program of Study International Business Management Marketing B.S. in Business Administration Concentration options: Entrepreneurship/Small Business Management Financial Management General Healthcare Management Interdisciplinary Program of Study (IPS) International Business Management Marketing A.S. Business Administration B.S. Business and Professional Studies A.S. Business Studies B.S. Computer Information Systems/Master of Business Administration (MBA) - 5 year program B.S. Computer Information Systems A.S. Computer Information Systems B.S. Software Development Certificate in Business Administration Minor in Computer Information Systems School of Legal Studies M.S. Criminal Justice Administration (MSCJA) B.S. Criminal Justice/M.S. Criminal Justice Administration B.S. Criminal Justice/B.S. Psychology (dual degree program) B.S. Criminal Justice A.S. Criminal Justice B.S. Forensic Science B.S. Legal Studies (pre-Law) B.S. Paralegal Studies A.S. Paralegal Studies Paralegal Certificate School of Hospitality, Sport and Tourism Management B.S. Hospitality and Tourism Management/Master of Business Administration - Concentrating in Hospitality and Tourism Management (MBA) - 5 year program B.S. Hospitality and Tourism Management Concentration options: • Sales and Marketing • Small Business Entrepreneurship B.S. Sport Management/Master of Business Administration (MBA) - 5 year program B.S. Sport Management Minors available • Coaching • Hospitality Management • Tourism and Recreation College of Health and Education School of Education Master of Education (M.Ed.) Concentration in Instructional Theory and Practice M.S. Human Relations M.S. Clinical Mental Health Counseling M.S. School Counseling B.S. Educational Studies B.S. Elem