(50, ' IGLOBAL UNIVERSITY', 2008, 'USA', '', '', 'Annandale (Main Campus),, Virginia,22003, United States.', 'Annandale (Main Campus),, Virginia,22003, United States.', '', ' Completed Admission Application Form (Link below) or download the PDF form here.\r\n\r\n2. Copy of Resume detailing education and work experience\r\n\r\n3. Two letters of recommendations (employer, professor, or teacher)\r\n \r\n4. Photo ID for Domestic students (drivers license, government ID, etc.)\r\n\r\n5. Official Transcripts showing the completion of a Bachelor’s degree or its equivalent for a Master’s degree program.\r\n?\r\nA maximum of 27 credit hours (50% of the total credit hours required for a Master’s degree) may be granted as transfer credits toward only coursework based on course-by-course contents evaluation of prior qualified graduate education at accredited educational institutions.\r\n?\r\n6. Statement of Purpose or Personal Essay (A brief statement of the applicant’s purpose of study)\r\n\r\n7. An Application Fee of $80.00 (This non-refundable fee must be paid within 5 working days after the submission of application)\r\n?\r\n \r\nINTERNATIONAL STUDENTS\r\n \r\nIn addition to the above documents, the following is required for international students:\r\n?\r\n8. Copy of student’s passport (inside cover and signature page)\r\n\r\n9. Original or certified bank account statement(s) or letter issued within 3 months of the time of application and reflecting a minimum balance equivalent to $23,640.00. (must be sent by mail)\r\n?\r\nOr, If the bank account statement is not in the student’s name, a certified or notarized Affidavit of Financial Support form reflecting a minimum balance equivalent to $23,640.00 must be completed by the sponsor within 3 months of the time of the application. (must be sent by mail)\r\n?\r\n10. For transfer students, Copy of the I-94 and any previous I-20 forms are required at the time of application.\r\n\r\n11. Evidence of English Proficiency\r\n \r\nThis may include a minimum,\r\n- TOEFL score of 550 (PBT), 205 (CBT), 60 (IBT) Or,\r\n- IELTS Score of 5.5 Or,\r\n- iTEP Score of 4.0 Or,\r\n- WAEC score of C6 or higher\r\n \r\nGlobal University offers "English Conditional Admission" (ECA) to international students who meet all the academic requirements for a bachelor''s or master''s degree program but either have not achieved the minimum scores of any of the above tests or have not taken any of the tests. Students can be still admitted to the degree program on condition that they will study English in the IGlobal University ESL Program.\r\n \r\nFor more detailed information about ECA, click here.\r\n \r\n12. I-20 International Express Mailing Fee of $50 (this fee is non-refundable) - required for I-20s mailed outside of the USA.\r\n \r\n13. Degree Evaluation: Degrees received in a country other than the United States must be evaluated and submitted directly to the University by a NACES or AICE member. We recommend using IERF.\r\n \r\nThe students who have earned or will earn 3-year bachelor''s degrees in India, Bangladesh, Pakistan, Bhutan, Nepal, Australia, South Africa and any participant in the Bologna Process, may not have to be evaluated. However, the Admissions Committee will determine a waiver of credential evaluation on a case-by-case basis.\r\n \r\n14. VISA Copy (F1-VISA holders must present their VISA upon arrival in the US or upon transferring into the university)', 'private', '', 'COURSES OFFERED:  1) Undergraduate or Bachelor’s course 2) Graduate of Master’s course 3) ESL certificate Program ELIGIBLITY CRITERIA: 1) Minimum of 2.0 CGPA on the scale of 4.0 is mandatory for the last degree. 2) IELTS/ TOEFL/ ITEP/ WAEC score  This may include a minimum,  - TOEFL score of 550 (PBT), 160 (CBT), 55 (IBT) Or, - IELTS Score of 5.0 Or, - iTEP Score of 4.0 Or, - WAEC score of C6 or higher   IGlobal University offers "English Conditional Admission" (ECA) to international students who meet all the academic requirements for a bachelor''s or master''s degree program but either have not achieved the minimum scores of any of the above tests or have not taken any of the tests. Students can be still admitted to the degree program on condition that they will study English in the IGlobal University ESL Program.  BANK STATEMENT REQUIREMENT: 1) Undergraduate course- $25,290 2) Graduate course- $23,640  University Course fee: 1) Graduate Program       Quarter Credit hours: 54 Tuition per Credit hour: $400 Total Program Tuition: $21,600  Concentrations of MBA available : Leadership and Management Information Technology Entrepreneurship Health Care Management Hospitality and Tourism Management Human Resources Management Project Management Education Homeland Security Public Service and Administration Global Business Management Criminal Justice Church/Ministry Leadership and Management Accounting Finance    2) Undergraduate Program        Quarter Credit hours: 180 Tuition per Credit hour: $300 Total Program Tuition: $54,000    3) ESL Certificate Program        Clock hours: 960 Tuition per Course: $400 ESL Tuition Deposit: $500 Total Program Tuition: $6,400  Intake Dates: July 7th  October 6th', 'David Sohn', '', '', '', 'on', '', '', '', '', '', 'igu.edu', 'https://www.facebook.com/IGlobalU ', 'https://twitter.com/IGlobal1 ', '', 'https://www.linkedin.com/edu/iglobal-university-162141 ', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/IGlobalUniv ', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/IGlobalUniv ', '', '', '[""]', '["IGlobal University is conveniently located 30 minutes west of Washington D.C. and 20 minutes east of Dulles International Airport. \\u00a0Washington D.C. is the capital of United States and one of the best place to live, study and work. \\u00a0Students will enjoy studying and working with elite professionals from all over the world experiencing diversity in culture, nationality, religion and background.  KEY POINTS: 1. The Most Inexpensive and Competitive Tuition Rates; \\u00a0 2. Education for International Students obtaining degrees in their home country; (After completing the requirement through 100% online education) \\u00a0 3. Scholarships or financial assistance to the underprivileged or less fortunate (e.g., disable, deaf, or blind), military, or seniors;"]', '<p>IGlobal University is conveniently located 30 minutes west of Washington D.C. and 20 minutes east of Dulles International Airport. &nbsp;Washington D.C. is the capital of United States and one of the best place to live, study and work. &nbsp;Students will enjoy studying and working with elite professionals from all over the world experiencing diversity in culture, nationality, religion and background.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>KEY POINTS:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. The Most Inexpensive and Competitive Tuition Rates;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Education for International Students obtaining degrees in their home country;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(After completing the requirement through 100% online education)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Scholarships or financial assistance to the underprivileged or less fortunate</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(e.g., disable, deaf, or blind), military, or seniors;</p>\r\n', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(51, 'International American University', 2005, 'USA', '', '', '2525 W 8th St #300, Los Angeles, CA 90057, United States', '2525 W 8th St #300, Los Angeles, CA 90057, United States', 'International American University was originally established in 2005 in Los\r\nAngeles, CA as a distance learning school offering degrees strictly online. In\r\nJanuary 2008, they moved to Palmdale, CA and established our first classroom\r\nprogram. Gaining SEVIS approval in March of 2009 to host F-1 Students, theysought the need for a more cultur', 'Admissions & Records. An official transcript is one that is sent directly to IAU from\r\nthe issuing institution. Prior college and university transfer courses and/or\r\ndegrees must be earned at an appropriately accredited institution or foreign\r\nequivalent. For schools outside the U.S., please see policy below.\r\n• Foreign Credential Evaluations: If you completed your degree at a foreign\r\n(outside of the United States) college or university, you will need to submit a\r\nprofessional General Report foreign credential evaluation. If you want to receive\r\ntransfer credit for coursework you have completed at a foreign (outside of the\r\nUnited States) college or university you will need to submit a professional course-\r\nby-course evaluation of your coursework.\r\n• Resume: As an undergraduate business student, it is helpful to have professional\r\nexperience at the time of application. As a graduate business student, it is vital.\r\n• Evidence of English Proficiency (required for foreign students)\r\n• Copy of passport\r\n• Bank Statements to show financial capability\r\n• Dependent Copy of Passport (If applicable)\r\nAdmission Process:\r\n1.\r\n2.\r\n3.\r\n4.\r\n5.\r\n6.\r\nStep 1: Submit Admissions Portfolio (AP) + Admissions Fee\r\nStep 2: Evaluation\r\nStep 3: Decision\r\nStep 4: Accept/Refuse Admission Offer\r\nStep 5: Official Enrollment\r\nStep 6: Registering For Classes\r\nWork Option:\r\nThis university allows full-time CPT from day one and also OPT is available after\r\ncompletion of your studiesThanks !!!', 'public', '', 'Department of Business • Associates of Science in Business Administration (ASBA) – 60 Units • Bachelor of Business Administration (BBA) – 120 Units • Master of Business Administration (MBA) – 36 Units • Doctor of Business Administration (DBA) – 60 Units CAS Department of Business • Accelerated Certificate of Accountancy (CAcc) – 27 Units • Certificate of Accountancy (CAcc) – 60 Units • Bachelor of Accountancy (BAcc) – 120 Units Department of English Studies • English as a Second Language (ESL) Intake:Applications are accepted throughout the year but there are 3 major intakes for this university. Spring- Jan and April Summer- May and Aug Fall- Sept and Dec Fee: Application Fee: $175.00 (non-refundable) Undergraduate Tuition: $200.00 per unit Graduate Tuition: $400.00 per unit As per the latest update on university website: Link is provided below http://www.iau.la/download/iau_cat14.pdf Entire course fee: Associate of Science in Business Administration (ASBA) - $100 per unit. $100 x 60 = $6,000 Bachelor of Business Administration (BBA) - $100 per unit. $200 x 120 = $24,000 Master of Business Administration (MBA) - $250 per unit. $400 x 36 = $14,400 Doctor of Business Administration (DBA) - $250 per unit. $250 x 60 = $15,000 Bank Statement: For Undergraduate course: $32400 minimum you need to show as bank statement For Graduate course: $16200 minimum you need to show as bank statement', '', '', '', '', 'on', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '[""]', '["\\u2022 International American University is located at Los Angeles, CA. \\u2022 IAU is an institution of higher education approved by the state of California bureau for private post secondary education (BPPE). \\u2022 Further, IAU is authorized by the United States Department of Homeland Security (DHS), to accept and enroll foreign, non-immigrant F-1 students for academic degrees or language trainings. Note: On March 6, 2009, International American University was approved by the U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE) of the Department of Homeland Security (DHS) to accept and enroll foreign, non-immigrant F-1 students for academic degrees"]', '<p>&bull; International American University is located at Los Angeles, CA.<br />\r\n&bull; IAU is an institution of higher education approved by the state of California<br />\r\nbureau for private post secondary education (BPPE).<br />\r\n&bull; Further, IAU is authorized by the United States Department of Homeland<br />\r\nSecurity (DHS), to accept and enroll foreign, non-immigrant F-1 students for<br />\r\nacademic degrees or language trainings.<br />\r\nNote: On March 6, 2009, International American University was approved by the<br />\r\nU.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE) of the Department of Homeland<br />\r\nSecurity (DHS) to accept and enroll foreign, non-immigrant F-1 students for<br />\r\nacademic degrees</p>\r\n', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(52, 'International Technological University', 1994, 'USA', '', '', 'San Jose, California\r\nUnited States Of America ', 'San Jose, California\r\nUnited States Of America ', 'ITU is institutionally accredited by the Western Association of Schools and Colleges (WASC) as of February 22, 2013. Previously, ITU was accredited by ACICS from July 1, 2001 to December 31, 2004, according to the US DoE Database of Accredited Postsecondary Institutions and Programs     General MBA\r\nVisit BA Website\r\nMBA: Concentration in Accounting\r\nVisit BA Website\r\nMBA: Concentration in Bio Management\r\nVisit BA Website\r\nMBA: Concentration in Digital Media Management\r\nVisit BA Website\r\nMBA: Concentration in Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP/SAP)\r\nVisit BA Website\r\nMBA: Concentration in Finance\r\nVisit BA Website\r\nMBA: Concentration in Healthcare Management\r\nVisit BA Website\r\nMBA: Concentration in Human Resource Management\r\nVisit BA Website\r\nMBA: Concentration in Information Systems Management\r\nVisit BA Website\r\nMBA: Concentration in International Business\r\nVisit BA Website\r\nMBA: Concentration in Management\r\nVisit BA Website\r\nMBA: Concentration in Marketing\r\nVisit BA Website\r\nMBA: Concentration in Project Management\r\nVisit BA Website\r\n', 'All applicants must submit the following as evidence of their academic background and abilities:\r\nSealed official transcripts from all universities attended. Transcripts, listing courses taken and grades received, must be mailed directly from the institution or through a verified e-Transcript provider. ITU has partnered with Parchment for e-Transcript submissions.\r\nAdditional transcripts must be submitted for transfer credits from all post-secondary institutions. Foreign transferred credits are subject to credential evaluation (please see additional international admissions requirements). Transcripts must be issued directly from the institution, listing courses taken and grades received.\r\nStatement of Purpose essay (500-750 words). Topic: “Please describe why you are interested in the intended program of study, and how you hope to use this education to achieve your future goals.”\r\nResume demonstrating relevant work or volunteer experience. 2 pages maximum.\r\nGRE or GMAT scores recommended. Scores must be sent directly from the testing center.\r\nTwo Letters of Recommendation recommended (required if undergraduate cumulative GPA is lower than 2.75). Letters should speak to the student’s professional and academic experience and potential to succeed in graduate school.\r\nAll applicants must submit identification documentation to the Office of Admissions in the form of: a valid government issued identification card or unexpired passport.\r\n \r\nAdditional Requirements for International Applicants\r\nForeign credential evaluation for any non-US degrees. ITU will accept foreign transcript evaluations from NACES-recognized service providers, such as International Education Research Foundation (IERF) and World Education Services (WES). You must select “International Technological University” as a receiving institution for this service.\r\nProof of English proficiency. Students may demonstrate English proficiency through one of the following ways:\r\nTest of English as a Foreign Language (TOEFL) examination. ITU looks for a score of 80* or better for the internet-based test (ibt).\r\nInternational English Language Testing System (IELTS) examination. ITU looks for a band score of 6.5* or better for the academic module.\r\nAccredited bachelor’s or master’s degree from a regionally accredited US institution or from a native English-speaking country.\r\nEvidence that the applicant’s first language is English. Applicant should submit documentation that s/he was schooled in a country where English is the official language and language of instruction.\r\nTranscript demonstrating the completion of an accredited ESL program in the US, or in a non-US Anglophone country, with a proficiency level equivalent to a B2 or above, according to the Common European Framework (CEFR).\r\n*Students whose TOEFL or IELTS scores do not meet this benchmark will be required to partake\r\nin additional language training either prior to or upon arrival at ITU, depending on the student’s\r\nlevel of proficiency.\r\n** All documents submitted for admission become property of the University and will not be returned.\r\nInstitution and Program Codes\r\n \r\nGMAT Program Codes\r\n\r\nMBA\r\n5L0-QK-38\r\nMSCE\r\n5L0-QK-95\r\nMSDA\r\n5L0-QK-42\r\nMSEE\r\n5L0-QK-02\r\nMSEM\r\n5L0-QK-71\r\nMSSE\r\n5L0-QK-14\r\nGRE\r\n\r\nInstitution Code\r\n8857\r\nTOEFL\r\n\r\nDI Code\r\n4446\r\nHow to Submit Your Admission Documents\r\nMail\r\nOfficial documents may be submitted via post:\r\nOfficial Test Scores (GRE, GMAT, TOEFL, IELTS)\r\nOfficial Transcripts*\r\nPlease have the testing center or your university send documents to:\r\nOffice of Admission\r\n2711 N 1st St.\r\nSan Jose, CA 95134\r\nOnline\r\nWe currently accept online submissions for the following:\r\nElectronic Transcripts (if your institution provides this service)\r\nCourse by course evaluation (you must select “International Technological University” as a receiving institution for this service).\r\nITU Online Document Submission Form\r\nSubmit Documents Online\r\nTips for Applying\r\n1. Choose a good email address for your Online Application\r\nNotifications about your application – including decisions – are sent via email so be sure to provide an email address you check regularly.\r\n2. Submit your documents early\r\nEverything must be submitted before we can review your application!\r\n3. International Students Only – Learn more about the international student document submission process.\r\nForeign credential evaluations can take time. Plan at least 2-3 weeks to process.\r\nLast modified: February 2, 2016\r\n\r\n\r\nFOR MORE INFO:\r\n http://itu.edu/\r\n\r\nInternational Technological University\r\n\r\nMotto\r\n"Global Development Through Silicon Valley Education"\r\nType\r\nPrivate, Non-profit[1]\r\nEstablished\r\n1994\r\nPresident\r\nDr. Gregory O''Brien [2]\r\nLocation\r\nSan Jose, California\r\nUnited States Of America \r\n37.331416°N 121.895362°WCoordinates: 37.331416°N 121.895362°W\r\nCampus\r\nUrban campus\r\nNickname\r\nITU\r\nWebsite\r\nEstimated Cost of living:\r\nTuition Fee:\r\nApplication Fee:\r\nType of Accommodation                                        \r\nSocial Media Links:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nVideos Link: 	\r\nPhotos of Universities:\r\n\r\nwww.itu.edu\r\n$10,000 USD Aprox per year\r\n$19,800 complete program fee\r\n$100  USD\r\nOff Campus & on campus \r\nFace book- https://www.facebook.com/ITUSJ \r\nTwitter - https://twitter.com/itu_tweets\r\nLinked In- https://www.linkedin.com/edu/international-technological-university-17867 \r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/user/itusj \r\n\r\n\r\n', 'private', '', 'ITU''s programs are divided into 6 separate departments: Computer science, electrical engineering, business administration, engineering management, interdisciplinary sciences, and digital arts. The university offers 6 master''s degrees, and three research doctorate degrees in Interdisciplinary Sciences, Business Administration, and Electrical Engineering. Some of ITU''s master''s degrees are approved by the California Bureau of Private Postgraduate Education (BPPE). ACADEMIC DEPARTM  BUSINESS ADMINISTRATION COMPUTER SCIENCE & SOFTWARE ENGINEERING DIGITAL ARTS ELECTRICAL & COMPUTER ENGINEERING ENGINEERING MANAGEMENT INTERDISCIPLINARY SCIENCES', 'Dr. Gregory O''Brien', '', '', '', 'on', '', '', '', '', '', 'www.itu.edu', 'https://www.facebook.com/ITUSJ ', 'https://twitter.com/itu_tweets', '', 'https://www.linkedin.com/edu/international-technological-university-17867 ', '', '', '', '', '', '[""]', '["International Technological University (ITU) was founded in 1994 by Professor\\u00a0Shu-Park Chan, previously a professor and interim dean of the School of Engineering a