(71, 'Merrimack College', 1947, 'USA', '', '', 'North Andover, MA, USA', 'North Andover, MA, USA', 'Merrimack College is accredited by the New England Association of Schools and Colleges, Inc. through its Commission on Institutions of Higher Education.', 'A minimum TOEFL score of 80 (internet-based) with no subset score lower than 18 for all students whose native language is not English\r\nA minimum IELTS score of 6.5 (with no band below 6.0) for all students whose native language is not English\r\nA minimum SAT Critical Reading Score of 500\r\nA minimum PTE Academic score of 53\r\nA minimum ACT composite score of 23\r\nDeadlines\r\nWhen would you like to enroll?\r\nApplication\r\nDeadline\r\nAdmission Decision\r\nJanuary \r\nDecember 15\r\nRolling                   \r\nSeptember Early Decision\r\nNovember 15\r\nRolling\r\nSeptember Early Action\r\nNovember 15\r\nRolling\r\nSeptember Regular Decision\r\nFebruary 15\r\nRolling\r\nTuition Fees ', 'public', '', 'Girard School of Business Master of Science in Accounting Master of Science in Management School of Liberal Arts Master of Public Affairs Master of Science in Clinical Mental Health Counseling  School of Science & Engineering Master of Science in Civil Engineering Master of Science in Mechanical Engineering Master of Science in Computer Science Master of Science in Community Health Education Master of Science in Exercise and Sport Science Master of Science in Health and Wellness Management Health Sciences Fellowships School of Education & Social Policy M.Ed. Teacher Education M.Ed. Competency-based Teacher Education M.Ed. in Higher Education M.Ed. in Community Engagement Fellowship Programs M.Ed. in Curriculum & Instruction (General Studies) M.Ed. in School Counseling Master of Science in Criminology and Criminal Justice', 'Dr. Christopher Hopey Ph.D.[1]', '', '', '', 'on', '', '', '', '', '', 'merrimack.edu', 'https://www.facebook.com/merrimackcollege ', 'http://www.merrimack.edu/index.php#hp-twitter ', '', '', '', 'http://www.merrimack.edu/index.php#hp-youtube ', 'http://www.merrimack.edu/index.php#hp-youtube ', '', '', '[""]', '["Merrimack College is a private college in the Roman Catholic, Augustinian tradition located in North Andover, Massachusetts. It offers more than 90 undergraduate academic programs in business, education, science, engineering, and the liberal arts. Merrimack also serves non-traditional students through part-time undergraduate degree programs; masters programs in accounting, education, health science, management, public affairs, social policy, and engineering; and a range of certificate, licensure and degree completion offerings. There are over 2,900 full-time undergraduates and 400 graduate students from more than 22 states and 17 countries enrolled at Merrimack, 75% of who reside on campus."]', '<p>Merrimack College is a private college in the Roman Catholic, Augustinian tradition located in North Andover, Massachusetts. It offers more than 90 undergraduate academic programs in business, education, science, engineering, and the liberal arts. Merrimack also serves non-traditional students through part-time undergraduate degree programs; masters programs in accounting, education, health science, management, public affairs, social policy, and engineering; and a range of certificate, licensure and degree completion offerings. There are over 2,900 full-time undergraduates and 400 graduate students from more than 22 states and 17 countries enrolled at Merrimack, 75% of who reside on campus.</p>\r\n', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(72, 'Midwestern State University', 1922, 'USA', '', '', 'Wichita Falls, Texas, U.S.', 'Wichita Falls, Texas, U.S.', 'Midwestern State University is accredited by the Southern Association of Colleges and Schools Commission on Colleges to award associate, baccalaureate, and master''s degrees.\r\nhttp://www.mwsu.edu/Assets/documents/busoffice/201610FeeChart201610b-.pdf', '', 'public', '', 'Biology MS departmental application, recommendations, GRE Business Administration MBA GMAT Clinical Mental Health   MA departmental application, GRE Computer Science  MS GRE Criminal Justice MACJ   Curriculum and Instruction MED GRE Educational Leadership MED GRE Educational Technology MED GRE English MA GRE Exercise Physiology MSEP GRE Family Nurse Practitioner MSN departmental application, GRE Family Psychiatric Mental Health Nurse Practitioner MSN departmental application, GRE Geoscience MS departmental application, personal statement, recommendations, GRE Health Services Administration MHA departmental application, GRE History MA GRE Human Resources Development MA GRE Nurse Educator MSN departmental application, GRE Political Science MA GRE Psychology MA GRE Radiologic Administration MSRS departmental application, GRE Radiologic Education MSRS departmental application, GRE Radiologist Assistant MSRS departmental application, GRE Reading Education MED GRE School Counseling MED departmental application, GRE Special Education MED GRE Sport Administration MED GRE Training and Development MA GRE', '', '6043', '', '', 'on', '', '', '', '', '', 'www.mwsu.edu', 'https://www.facebook.com/MidwesternState ', 'https://twitter.com/midwesternstate ', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/MidwesternState ', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/MidwesternState ', '', '', '[""]', '["Midwestern State University is a public liberal arts college in Wichita Falls, Texas and a member of the Council of Public Liberal Arts Colleges. In 2015, it had over 6,000 students. Midwestern is one of four independent public universities in Texas unaffiliated with a state public university system. It is the state''s only public liberal arts college. Founded in 1922 as\\u00a0Wichita Falls Junior College, it was renamed\\u00a0Hardin Junior College\\u00a0in 1937 when it moved to its present location off Taft Boulevard. In 1946, a senior division was added and it was renamed\\u00a0Hardin College. In January 1950, the name changed to\\u00a0Midwestern University, the junior college division remaining Hardin Junior College. In these years, wider recognition came to the school. In March 1948, the University became a member of the Association of Colleges and Secondary Schools. In January 1959, the University added a Graduate School which received full approval from the State Board of Education in August of that year."]', '<p>Midwestern State University is a public liberal arts college in Wichita Falls, Texas and a member of the Council of Public Liberal Arts Colleges. In 2015, it had over 6,000 students. Midwestern is one of four independent public universities in Texas unaffiliated with a state public university system. It is the state&#39;s only public liberal arts college.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Founded in<strong> 1922</strong> as&nbsp;<strong>Wichita Falls Junior College</strong>, it was renamed&nbsp;<strong>Hardin Junior College</strong>&nbsp;in 1937 when it moved to its present location off Taft Boulevard. In 1946, a senior division was added and it was renamed&nbsp;<strong>Hardin College</strong>. In January 1950, the name changed to&nbsp;<strong>Midwestern University</strong>, the junior college division remaining<strong> Hardin Junior College</strong>. In these years, wider recognition came to the school. In March 1948, the University became a member of the Association of Colleges and Secondary Schools. In January 1959, the University added a Graduate School which received full approval from the State Board of Education in August of that year.</p>\r\n', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(73, 'Milwaukee School of Engineering', 1903, 'USA', '', '', 'Milwaukee, Wisconsin, US', 'Milwaukee, Wisconsin, US', ' MSOE is accredited by the Higher Learning Commission (800-621-7440), www.ncahlc.org. MSOE received initial accreditation from the Higher Learning Commission in 1971.', 'Undergraduate \r\n Required Documents\r\nA completed international student application.\r\nOfficial transcripts of all secondary or post-secondary schools that you attended (high school or college) showing complete results from every year.\r\nOfficial TOEFL or IELTS test results. MSOE’s TOEFL code is 1476. For full admission we require 82ibt TOEFL with the band score of 19 or or 6.5 IELTS with a minimum band score of 6.0. If your score is below our requirement, please see conditional admission information.\r\nOriginal MSOE financial certification or original bank document (on bank letterhead) showing enough money to cover your education and living expenses at MSOE\r\nOriginal signature sheet document\r\nA copy of your current passport\r\n\r\nGraduate Requirement:\r\n\r\nRequired Documents\r\nA completed international student application.\r\nOfficial college/university transcripts. A bachelor’s degree is required for admission to our graduate programs.\r\nThree letters of recommendation submitted online or by email. Letters can be from professors and past or present managers or employers.\r\nOfficial GRE or GMAT scores, depending on the program. MSOE’s GRE code is 1476.\r\nPersonal statement. A one-page letter stating why you would like to study in MSOE’s graduate program.\r\nOfficial TOEFL or IELTS test results. MSOE’s TOEFL code is 1476. For full admission we require 90ibt TOEFL with the band score of 21 or or 7.0 IELTS with a minimum band score of 6.0. If your score is below our requirement, please see conditional admission information.\r\nOriginal MSOE financial certification or original bank document (on bank letterhead) showing enough money to cover your education and living exp