e  Nursing Undergraduate Programs Accelerated Second-Degree B.S. in Nursing  Nursing  Graduate Programs Nursing   Tuition Fees: Please refer the below link  http://www.msoe.edu/community/admissions/financial-aid/page/2123/tuition  Requirements: Undergraduate   Required Documents A completed international student application. Official transcripts of all secondary or post-secondary schools that you attended (high school or college) showing complete results from every year. Official TOEFL or IELTS test results. MSOE’s TOEFL code is 1476. For full admission we require 82ibt TOEFL with the band score of 19 or or 6.5 IELTS with a minimum band score of 6.0. If your score is below our requirement, please see conditional admission information. Original MSOE financial certification or original bank document (on bank letterhead) showing enough money to cover your education and living expenses at MSOE Original signature sheet document A copy of your current passport  Graduate Requirement:  Required Documents A completed international student application. Official college/university transcripts. A bachelor’s degree is required for admission to our graduate programs. Three letters of recommendation submitted online or by email. Letters can be from professors and past or present managers or employers. Official GRE or GMAT scores, depending on the program. MSOE’s GRE code is 1476. Personal statement. A one-page letter stating why you would like to study in MSOE’s graduate program. Official TOEFL or IELTS test results. MSOE’s TOEFL code is 1476. For full admission we require 90ibt TOEFL with the band score of 21 or or 7.0 IELTS with a minimum band score of 6.0. If your score is below our requirement, please see conditional admission information. Original MSOE financial certification or original bank document (on bank letterhead) showing enough money to cover your education and living expenses at MSOE Original signature sheet document  A copy of your current passport.', '', '2658', '