(74, 'Monroe College', 1933, 'USA', '', '', 'New York has 2 campuses, Bronx & \r\nNew Rochelle.', 'New York has 2 campuses, Bronx & \r\nNew Rochelle.', 'Monroe College is accredited by the Middle States Commission on Higher Education. The Middle States Commission on Higher Education is an institutional accrediting agency recognized by the U.S. Secretary of Education and the Council for \r\nHigher Education Accreditation.\r\n\r\nMonroe College is authorized by the Board of Regents of the University of the State of New York to grant a Certificate in Practical Nursing; Associate in Science (AS) degrees in Criminal Justice and Information Technology; Associate in Applied Science (AAS) degrees in Accounting, Baking and Pastry, Business Administration, Culinary Arts, Hospitality Management, Medical Administration, Medical Assisting, Pharmacy Technician and Registered Nursing; Bachelor of Science (BS) degrees in Criminal Justice, Early Childhood Education, Nursing, Information Technology and Public Health; Bachelor of Business Administration degrees (BBA) in Accounting, Business Management, General Business, Health Services Administration and Hospitality Management. Monroe is also authorized to grant Master''s degrees in Business (MBA), Public Health (MPH). All curricula are registered by the State Education Department.', '', 'public', '', 'Programs offered by Monroe College: The college is a nationally ranked private institution of higher learning that offers certificate, associate, bachelors, and master’s degree programs through its Schools of Criminal Justice, Information Technology, Nursing, Education, Business & Accounting, Hospitality Management and the Culinary Arts, and Allied Health Professions.  Masters: • MBA - Finance • MBA - IT Management • MBA - Marketing • MBA - Health Care Managemen • MBA – Entrepreneurship • MBA –Community Development • Master of Public Health • Master of Criminal Justice  Bachelors: • BBA – Accounting • BBA – Finance • BBA – Human Resources • BBA – Marketing • BBA – Entrepreneurship • BBA – Forensic Accounting • BBA – Sports Management • BBA – Entertainment and Media Management • BBA - Business Management • BBA – Information Technology • BBA – Hospitality Management • BBA – Health Service Administration • B.S – Nursing • B.S – Public Health • B.S – Early Childhood Education   Intakes We have 3 intakes which are as follows: • Early January • Early May • Early September  Last Date for Application: ??November 15th for January Intake ??March 15th for May Intake ??July 15th for September Intake   Entry Requirements for Under Graduate Programmes Academic: • Second class & above at 12th standard are eligible,  English Requirements: A TOEFL total score 60-74 (a total score of 27-60 for admission into any of our ESL Language Programs is required) IELTS- 5.5 and above Overall Mandatory if less score need to attend Skype interview.  Skype Interview: All students no matter whether they have good academics or good English proficiency Would be interviewed via Skype by the Administration team of Monroe College and Would decide about the admission.     Entry Requirements for Graduate/Masters Programmes Academic: • Second class & above in Bachelor degree are eligible,  English Requirements: A total TOEFL score of 80 with at least 20 in writing and speaking is required IELTS- 6.0 and above Overall Mandatory if less score need to attend Skype interview.  Skype Interview: All students no matter whether they have good academics or good English proficiency would be interviewed via Skype by the Administration team of Monroe College and would decide about the admission.   Document Checklist:  Bachelors:  ??Application form with 35$ fee ??Academic transcripts ??Resume ??Two Letters of Recommendation ??Essay ( Statement of purpose) ??IELTS or TOEFL Certificate ??Job Experience letter (if any)  Master`s:  ??Application form with 50$ fee ??Academic transcripts ??Resume ??Two Letters of Recommendation ??Essay ( Statement of purpose) ??IELTS or TOEFL Certificate ??Job Experience letter (if any)  Document checklist & Processing Time for I20: Following documents are required to issue I20 Financial sponsor documents • Affidavit of support (notarized) • Financial statements • Bank statement • Loan approval letter • Scholarship or grant awards    • Employment information (proof of income) • Job letter • Tax Return (US citizen sponsors) • Proof of business ownership (self employed)  Housing sponsor documents • Off-Campus: Sponsor Affidavit and copy of lease/deed • On-Campus: Housing application and application fee receipt   Processing Time for Acceptance Letter: Once all the above mentioned documents are given then the i20 would be issued within 2 weeks.', 'Stephen J. Jerome[1]', '', '', '', 'on', '', '', '', '', '', 'http://www.monroecollege.edu/', 'http://www.monroecollege.edu/', 'https://twitter.com/monroe_college ', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC_bsavQPWu_8ZYB00P0-61w ', 'https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC_bsavQPWu_8ZYB00P0-61w ', '', '', '[""]', '["Monroe College, New York, established since 1933 and one of the Oldest Colleges existing for more than 80 years would be one of the best places for Indian students to study under graduate and graduate program at an affordable fee.  Since 1933, Monroe College has been an institution committed to providing a real world education. With experienced professors, hands-on learning, and relevant, real world degree programs, Monroe ensures that its students have a chance to realize their dreams. Over the last 80 years, Monroe has grown from a 7 person business to a college of 7,000 students."]', '<p>Monroe College, New York, established since 1933 and one of the Oldest Colleges</p>\r\n\r\n<p>existing for more than 80 years would be one of the best places for Indian students to</p>\r\n\r\n<p>study under graduate and graduate program at an affordable fee.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Since 1933, Monroe College has been an institution 