(79, 'North Eastern University- Boston, USA', 1898, 'USA', '', '', 'Boston, MA, 02115, USA', 'Boston, MA, 02115, USA', '', 'Participants must have completed a Bachelor’s degree (or international equivalent) \r\nA one-on-one interview with a member of the admissions team and be conducted in lieu of a TOEFL or IELTS exam score\r\nTotal fee:  \r\nThe entire course fee for this university is $ 21,000.  This can be paid in two installments.\r\n1. $13,000 needs to be paid in the 1st semester within 1 week of starting the classes.\r\n2. $ 8,000 need to be paid as soon as 2nd semester has been started.\r\n\r\nBank statement requirement:\r\nStudents need to show $ 37,000 as the bank statement for admission.  Either he can show in his own account or any of his Blood relative bank account.\r\nDocuments required for Admission:\r\n1) Application form\r\n2) Passport copy\r\n3) Banks statement (Minimum $37000)\r\n4) Letter of support (If any someone else is sponsoring)\r\n5) Two recommendation letter (In the letter head)\r\n6)  EPC letter\r\n7) Official transcript and degree of previous education \r\n8) Statement of Purpose- Your Personal Statement should be attached, must be typed, and should not exceed three pages. This statement, which should be written entirely by you, should include an explanation of why you would like to enroll in the Graduate Certificate Program at Northeastern University, as well as a description of your professional goals and experiences. Your Personal Statement gives you the opportunity to more fully present yourself to the Admissions Committee and to provide insight into your interests and thoughts processes.\r\n\r\nApplication Processing fee:  \r\nIt has been waived by the university representative for us.\r\n\r\nDependents permission:\r\nSpouse and child are allowed as dependent in US on F2 visa.\r\nDependents work permission:\r\nDependents are not allowed to work in USA.\r\n\r\nRecently added courses: \r\n1) MBA   (Full-time, Evening, Online)\r\n2) MS in Accounting, Taxation, Finance, International Business\r\n3) Certificate course in Supply Chain Management\r\n', 'public', '', 'This Advanced Study of Management Graduate Certificate has been specifically designed to accommodate the unique needs of international students who seek to accelerate their professional and educational advancement. Described by some as a mini-MBA, this intensive, five-course program covers the most critical aspects of US business approaches by offering the following courses: Entrepreneurship and Innovation  People and Organizations of the New Economy  Financial Reporting and Managerial Accounting  Creating and Sustaining Market Strategies  Managing the Global Enterprise   University Services Available to Program Participants  Personal Academic Advisor Health Insurance  Housing   International Student Service Institute  Student Organizations    Program Structure  The program runs over an eight-month time period. Students can begin the program in any of three entry terms: September (Fall), January (Spring) or May (Summer). During the first four months students complete three 3-credit courses. In the second four months, students complete their final two courses.  Benefits  Students may transfer credit into a graduate program in their home country, or, students may apply and transfer graduate credits to a US institution and continue an MBA degree. Students may apply for OPT to be eligible to work in the US. Students may accelerate their professional development in a global arena. Students have the opportunity to experience one of the world’s great educational cities.  Admissions Criteria  Participants must have completed a Bachelor’s degree (or international equivalent)  A one-on-one interview with a member of the admissions team and be conducted in lieu of a TOEFL or IELTS exam score Total fee:   The entire course fee for this university is $ 21,000.  This can be paid in two installments. 1. $13,000 needs to be paid in the 1st semester within 1 week of starting the classes. 2. $ 8,000 need to be paid as soon as 2nd semester has been started.  Bank statement requirement: Students need to show $ 37,000 as the bank statement for admission.  Either he can show in his own account or any of his Blood relative bank account. Documents required for Admission: 1) Application form 2) Passport copy 3) Banks statement (Minimum $37000) 4) Letter of support (If any someone else is sponsoring) 5) Two recommendation letter (In the letter head) 6)  EPC letter 7) Official transcript and degree of previous education  8) Statement of Purpose- Your Personal Statement should be attached, must be typed, and should not exceed three pages. This statement, which should be written entirely by you, should include an explanation of why you would like to enroll in the Graduate Certificate Program at Northeastern University, as well as a description of your professional goals and experiences. Your Personal Statement gives you the opportunity to more fully present yourself to the Admissions Committee and to provide insight into your interests and thoughts processes.  Application Processing fee:   It has been waived by the university representative for us.  Dependents permission: Spouse and child are allowed as dependent in US on F2 visa. Dependents work permission: Dependents are not allowed to work in USA.  Recently added courses:  1) MBA   (Full-time, Evening, Online) 2) MS in Accounting, Taxation, Finance, International Business 3) Certificate course in Supply Chain Management', 'Joseph Aoun', '24944', '', '', 'on', '', '', '', '', '', 'northeastern.edu', 'https://www.facebook.com/northeastern ', 'https://twitter.com/northeastern ', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/Northeastern ', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/Northeastern ', '', '', '[""]', '["North Eastern university - It is among the top ranking Universities of USA and it is located in the oldest city of USA, that is Boston.  Boston city have a wide variety of internship as well as campus job opportunities.              They offer a unique opportunity of International students to study Graduate certificate for advanced study in Management course and earn 15 MBA level graduate credits at North Eastern University."]', '<p><strong>North Eastern university</strong> - It is among the top ranking Universities of USA and it is located in the oldest city of USA, that is Boston. Boston city have a wide variety of internship as well as campus job opportunities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>They offer a unique opportunity of International students to study Graduate certificate for advanced study in Management course and earn 15 MBA level graduate credits at North Eastern University.</p>\r\n', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
