raphic Information Systems Health Informatics (available online) Total Worker Health Nonprofit Management Professional Writing Public Relations Secure Software Engineering - Chase College of Law Master of Arts in Legal Studies LL.M. in U.S. Law Chase Law Full-Time Chase Law Part-Time Day Chase Law Part-Time Evening - Dual Law Degrees with Chase College of Law JD / Master of Business Informatics JD / Master of Health Informatics JD / MBA', 'Geoffrey S. Mearns', '', '', '', 'on', '', '', '', '', '', 'www.nku.edu', 'https://www.facebook.com/nkuedu ', 'https://twitter.com/nkuedu ', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/nku', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/nku', '', '', '[""]', '["Northern Kentucky University\\u00a0is a\\u00a0public,\\u00a0co-educational\\u00a0university\\u00a0in\\u00a0northern Kentucky\\u00a0located in\\u00a0Highland Heights, seven miles (11\\u00a0km) southeast of downtown\\u00a0Cincinnati,\\u00a0Ohio. The university is primarily an\\u00a0undergraduate,\\u00a0liberal arts institution, but it also features\\u00a0graduate\\u00a0programs. Total enrollment at the university currently exceeds 15,000 students, with over 13,000 undergraduate students and over 2,000 graduate students served by nearly 2600 faculty and staff. Northern Kentucky University is the third largest university, behind the\\u00a0University of Cincinnati\\u00a0and\\u00a0Miami University, but before\\u00a0Xavier University, of\\u00a0Greater Cincinnati''s four large, four-year\\u00a0universities\\u00a0and the youngest of Kentucky''s eight state universities, although it is not the last to join the state system, as the\\u00a0University of Louisville\\u00a0did not become a state university until 1970."]', '<p><strong>Northern Kentucky University</strong>&nbsp;is a&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/State_university_system">public</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Co-educational">co-educational</a>&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/University">university</a>