iplomas and Degrees - PHS2\nPre-Technology - PRT1\nProfessional Financial Services - FSP1\nProject Management - PRJ1\nProtection, Security and Investigation - PSI1\nPublic Relations - Corporate Communications - COR3\nPublic Safety Fundamentals - PSF1\nPublic Safety Leadership - PSL1\nRecreation and Leisure Services - RLD2\nRenewable Energies Technician - RET2S\nResidential Air Conditioning Systems Mechanic Apprentice (Block Release) [Apprenticeship] - RAS1W\nRespiratory Therapy - RST4\nRetirement Residence Management - RRM1\nSheet Metal Apprentice (Block Release) [Apprenticeship] - SMA1\nSocial Service Worker - SSW1\nSocial Service Worker (Fast Track) - SSW2\nSoftware and Information Systems Testing - SST2\nSpecial Events Planning - SEP1\nTheatre Arts - Performance - THP2\nTheatre Arts - Technical Production - THR1\nTool and Die Maker (Block Release) [Apprenticeship] - TDM2S\nTourism - Travel - TTC5\nTourism - Travel Studies - TTS1\nTruck and Coach Pre-Apprentice - TCP1\nTruck and Coach Technician (Block Release) [Apprenticeship] - TCT2\nTruck and Coach Technician (Day Release) [Apprenticeship] - TCT3\nVideo Game Design and Development - VGD1\nVisual Effects and Editing for Contemporary Media - VEE1\nWelding Techniques - WTQ1J\n', 'Peter Devlin', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'On  Campus/Off Campus', '1519-452-4277', 'admission@studymetro.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'https://www.fanshawec.ca/', 'https://www.facebook.com/FanshaweCollege/', 'https://twitter.com/fanshawecollege?lang=en', 'https://plus.google.com/107723043315313607852', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/fanshawe-college', 'https://www.instagram.com/fanshawecollege/?hl=en', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/MyFanshawe', NULL, '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, 'Fanshawe College', 'We offer a wide variety of undergraduate and post-graduate programs and courses that lead to employment opportunities in the areas of health care, human services, electronics, business administration, information technology, music production, art, design, manufacturing, hospitality, transportation, broadcasting, environmental science and civil engineering. Fanshawe is one of the largest colleges in Ontario with a community focus and campuses located in London, Simcoe, St. Thomas and Woodstock. Our locations in Southwestern Ontario offer you the best of friendly, small town living with access to larger centres along the Detroit-Toronto-Montreal corridor.', 'Why Fanshawe College?\n\nWe know you’re more than a student. That’s why Fanshawe is more than a college. Just look at Fanshawe’s incredible campus - or ask someone who knows. It’s a place where people meet and futures are made. \n\n\nIn addition to state-of-the-art tools for mastering your craft, we’ve got restaurants, residences and everything you need to have the best time with some of the best friends - people who share your passions and dreams.\nFanshawe is a place to engage and be hands-on with what you love - creating something, solving problems, helping others - and building a foundation for a lifetime of happiness and success. \n\n\nPlain and simple, Fanshawe College is the smart investment for your future. \n', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(156, 'George Brown College', 1967, 'Canada', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/George_Brown_College_logo.png', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/George_Brown_College.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IELTS (Academic) 6.5, minimum 6.0 in each skill band\nTOEFL 84 (Internet-based) minimum of 21 in each skill band\nGeorge Brown English for Academic Purposes Program Level 8 (non co-op programs) Level 9 (co-op programs)', 'Public', '$CAD 10,000 approx', 'http://www.georgebrown.ca/ProgramIndexAZ.aspx?id=11297&criteria=,506!Post%20Graduate,506!Diploma,506!Degree,506!Certificate,511!Full%20Time,511!Apprenticeship,511!Co-op,511!Distance,516!2015%20-%202016,516!2016%20-%202017&searchText=&Page=New%20Search&ekfxmensel=ed87be5d3_68_95&Sortid=Title', 'Anne sado', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'On  Campus/Off Campus', '1-877-515-5559', 'admission@studymetro.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'http://www.georgebrown.ca/', 'https://www.facebook.com/georgebrowncollege', 'https://twitter.com/gbcollege', 'https://plus.google.com/112215908831484887197', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/george-brown-college', 'https://www.instagram.com/gbcollege/', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/georgebrowncollege', NULL, '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, 'George Brown College', 'George Brown College has nine academic centres and schools offering more than 150 college and university programs. Our programs are designed to equip you with the right skills to step out into the world and land that job you want. No matter what field you’re interested in, we’ll help you get where you want to be.', 'Why George Brown College\nDeciding where to pursue your post-secondary education is one of the most important decisions you’ll make. George Brown College helps you develop the technical skills needed to get the job done and the people skills employers tell us they expect when looking to hire new graduates.\n', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(157, 'Global Village English Centres (Toronto)', 1979, 'Canada', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Global-village.png', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Global-Village-Background.png', 'Toronto,  Canada', '180 Bloor St W, Toronto, ON M5S 2V6, Canada', NULL, 'TOEFL 90  IELTS 6.5  MELAB  85 CAEL  70', 'Public', '$CAD 10,000 approx', 'General English: 20 Lessons/Week (AM M-F).\nMinimum age : 16\nStudents max per class : 16 (12 avg)\nNumber of lessons per week : 20 lessons of 50 min.\nSchool days : Monday to Friday\nLevels : beginner to high advanced\nStart dates : 2016-01-04, 2016-01-11, 2016-01-18, 2016-01-25, 2016-02-01, more\nMore information\nGeneral English: 25 Lessons/Week.\n\n\n\n\n\nGeneral English: 30 Lessons/Week.\n\n\n\n\n\nIELTS Preparation: 25 Lessons/Week.\n\n\n\n\n\nIELTS Exam.\n\n\n\nFCE: 25 Lessons/Week.\n\n\n\n\nFCE 30 Lessons/week.\n\n\n\n\nCAE: 25 Lessons/Week.\n\n\n\n\nCAE 30 Lessons/Week.\n\n\n\n\nCambridge materials, exam and administration.\n\nCAE, CPE, FCE, IELTS Support: 12 lessons.\n\n\nEnglish for Academic Purposes (EAP) - 30 lessons/week.\n\n\n\nPrivate Lessons - General English Per Lesson.\n\nPrivate Lessons - Test Preparation Per Lesson.\n\nEnglish for Business: 20 Lessons General English + 5 Lessons English for Business.\n\n\n\n\n\nCambridge Business English Certificate (BEC) Vantage Exam Prep.\n\n\n\n\nJob Readiness Workshop (2-lessons).\n\nEnglish + Ski and Snowboard.\n\n\n\n\nEnglish + Hockey.\n\n\n\n\nEnglish + Tennis.\n\n\n\n\nEnglish + Golf.\n\n\n\n\nEnglish + Dancing.\n\n\n\n\nEnglish + Baking.\n\n\n\n\nEnglish + Floral Design.\n\n\n\n\nEnglish + Makeup.\n\n\n\n\nTeen Activity Program (Fullboard Homestay Included).\n\n\n\n\n\n\nAcademic Teen Program (Residence).\n\n\n\n\n\nSummer Teen Hockey Camp.\n\n\n\n\nParent and Child Program.\n\n\n\nWinter Activity Program, 20 Lessons Per Week.\n\n\n\nBusiness English: 30 Lessons/Week.\n\n\n\n\n\nIELTS Preparation: 30 Lessons/Week.\n\n\n\n\n\nGlobal Village Pathway Programs \n\nOnline IELTS courses \n\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'On Campus/Off Campus', '1 416-968-1405', 'admission@studymetro.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'http://gvenglish.com/', 'https://www.facebook.com/GlobalVillageToronto/', 'https://twitter.com/gvenglishcentre', 'https://plus.google.com/+GvenglishCentres', NULL, 'https://www.instagram.com/gvtoronto/', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/GVEnglish', NULL, '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, 'Global Village English Centres (Toronto)', 'Global Village Toronto is one of the most established private English schools in Canada with over 36 years of experience. \n\nGV Toronto specializes in General English, Business English, IELTS Preparation, Cambridge FCE, CAE and CPE Exam Preparation courses. We specialize in teaching grammar structures and vocabulary in a way that makes it easy and fun to improve your level of speaking in English. We are also an open test centre for IELTS and Cambridge English, so students can prepare for and write their exams at our school to earn these valuable English certificates for their future.\n', 'What makes GV Toronto unique?\n• The professional GVT team - average 9 years of experience at GV!\n\n• Incredible location across from the University of Toronto and the Royal Ontario Museum.\n\n• Largest IELTS Testing Centre in Toronto\n\n• Established Cambridge Program & Testing Centre\n\n• High Quality Junior program downtown Toronto\n', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(158, 'Hansa Language Centre', 1969, 'Canada', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/hansa_logo_two_line.png', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Hansa-19-05-15.jpg', ' Toronto, Canada', ' 2160 Yonge Street, Toronto, ON M4S 2A8, Canada', NULL, 'TOEFL 90  IELTS 6.5  MELAB  85 CAEL  70', 'Private', '$CAD 10,000 approx', ' English Programs (ESL)\nTOEFL Preparation \n IELTS Preparation \nTeacher Training \n Arabic Courses \n French Courses\nGerman Courses\n Italian Courses\n Japanese Courses \nKorean Courses\n Mandarin Courses \n Portuguese Courses \nRussian Courses\n Spanish Courses\nOther Languages', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'On Campus/Off Campus', '1 416-485-1410', 'admission@studymetro.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'http://www.hansacanada.com/', 'https://www.facebook.com/HansaCanada/', 'https://twitter.com/hansalanguage', 'https://plus.google.com/102066496934848770401', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/hansa-language-centre', 'https://www.instagram.com/explore/locations/1898200/', 'https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCBKI5v8KuAjqXUVoM35bZeg', NULL, '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, 'Hansa Language Centre', 'Founded in 1969, Hansa Language Centre is one of the largest and most established language schools in Canada. Hansa offers a huge variety of English classes, a flexible schedule, and a long list of trips, excursions, sports and social activities. We also offer teacher training programs as well as a number of foreign language programs for Canadians, such as French, Spanish, German and Mandarin.', 'Why Hansa Language Centre?\n• TEACHERS - Excellent, qualified teachers\n• FLEXIBLE PROGRAMS - Students can study what they need with Hansa''s Flexible Learning System\n• SMALL CLASSES - An average of 6 - 8 students per class\n• RESULTS - Hansa students consistently outscore other language students on TOEFL, TOEIC and IELTS exams\n• EDUCATIONAL PATHWAYS - Hansa has liaisons with over a dozen Canadian high schools, colleges, and universities as well as scholarship opportunities\n• MEMORIES - Hansa is a fun and friendly school\n• LOCATION - Both campuses are conveniently located in midtown Toronto, steps from Eglinton subway station\n• ACTIVITIES - Awesome trips & daily activities\n• ACCREDITATION - Hansa is recognized by Languages Canada. Our students are eligible for student visa authorization.\n• CAPACITY - Hansa has a capacity for 1500 students\n', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
