l," "]', NULL, 'University of Waterloo', 'In just half a century, the University of Waterloo, located at the heart of Canada’s technology hub, has become a leading comprehensive university with nearly 36,000 full- and part-time students in undergraduate and graduate programs. Consistently ranked Canada’s most innovative university, Waterloo is home to advanced research and teaching in science and engineering, health, environment, arts and social sciences. From quantum computing and nanotechnology to clinical psychology and health sciences research, Waterloo brings ideas and brilliant minds together, inspiring innovations with real impact today and in the future. As home to the world''s largest post-secondary co-operative education program, Waterloo embraces its connections to the world and encourages enterprising partnerships in learning, research, and commercialization. With campuses and education centres on four continents, and academic partnerships spanning the globe, Waterloo is shaping the future of the planet.', 'Why University of Waterloo? \nWaterloo is one of only 11 universities in the world to earn a 5+ star rating in a new QS Stars rating which evaluates universities against 50 factors, ranging from teaching to facilities and research.\n\nThe 5+ rating recognizes the high quality education students receive at Waterloo and the success of our graduates.\n', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(186, 'Western Town College', 2000, 'Canada', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Western-town-college.png', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/western-town-college-background.png', 'Toronto,  Canada', '23 Toronto St, Toronto, ON M5C 2R1, Canada', NULL, 'TOEFL 90  IELTS 6.5  MELAB  85 CAEL  70', 'Public', '$CAD 10,000', 'General English\nUniversity Preparation Program\nIELTS Prep program\nSault College’s ESL Program in Toronto\nPower Talk ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'On Campus/Off Campus', '1 416-593-1446', 'admission@studymetro.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'http://www.westerntowncollege.ca/', 'https://www.facebook.com/wtctoronto', 'https://twitter.com/WTCToronto', 'https://plus.google.com/106795367463565456342', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/western-town-college-toronto', NULL, 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KjpuXRIUXns', NULL, '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, 'Western Town College', 'Western Town College (WTC) is located in the heart of downtown Toronto in the “Old Town Toronto” district at King and Toronto St. It is located two blocks from King Subway Station, and streetcars are just a few minutes walk from the school. It is in a very convenient area surrounded by banks, restaurants and many shops.\n\n\nWTC offers a diverse selection of classes to not only improve your English language ability, but also enjoy your learning experience! We pride ourselves on our great teachers who engage and energize their classes with their unique personalities and imaginative lessons.\n', 'Western Town College promises you…\n• Quality education\n• Qualified, experienced, and dedicated teachers\n• Supportive staff and administrators\n• Broad range of courses\n• Strictly enforced on-site “English Only Policy”\n', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(187, 'Wilfrid Laurier University', 1911, 'Canada', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Laur_seal.jpg', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/wlu.jpg', ' Waterloo,  Canada', '75 University Ave W, Waterloo, ON N2L 3C5, Canada', NULL, 'Information for International Students\n\nADMISSION REQUIREMENTS FOR INTERNATIONAL APPLICANTS\n*International applicants include all applicants that have obtained a previous undergraduate or Masters Degree outside of Canada.\nEducation equivalent to a Canadian four-year Undergraduate Degree, with a minimum B average (73% or G.P.A. of 8.0) in the last 10 half credit courses completed. Co-op applicants are required to have a B+ average (77% or G.P.A. of 9.0).\nWork experience\nFull-time MBA: A minimum of two (2) years full-time work experience or six (6) Co-op work terms. Part-time and summer employment between university terms do not apply.\nFull-time MBA with Co-op: No work experience is required. The maximum for co-op is two (2) years of full-time work experience, no exceptions.\nOne year International MBA: A minimums of three (3) years full-time work experience. Part-time and summer employment between university terms do not apply.\nA minimum score of 550 on the Graduate Management Admission Test (GMAT). The GMAT is mandatory for all students who have achieved their undergraduate degree outside of Canada. The GMAT is also mandatory for all students applying to the MBA with Co-op Option. We require a minimum score of 600 or better for Co-op candidates.\nFor students whose degrees were conferred by a non-English language institution, TOEFL (iBT) (minimum score of 21 in each section, minimum total score 100 (pBT 600)), or IELTS (minimum 7), or MELAB (minimum 90) or CAEL (minimum 70) results are mandatory requirements.\n*Those who do not meet English proficiency levels are encouraged to consider the Pre-MBA program here at Laurier. The 8-month Pre-MBA provides additional English and Business skills training, while also giving a conditional offer for full-time MBA study in the following year. The program runs every September to April. Students that pass the Pre-MBA program advance to Laurier’s MBA in August. For more information or to apply, please visit the Pre-MBA webpage or contact the Pre-MBA coordinator, Jason Whalen at maguiar@wlu.ca.\n\nThree (3) letters of reference. If the applicant’s degree is less than five years old, one academic and two professional references are required. If the degree is more than five years old, all three references may be professional. For the Co-op option, candidates may submit all three academic references, or two academic and one professional.', 'Public', '$CAD 10,000', '\n\nBachelor of Arts\nFaculty of Arts\nWaterloo\n\nAnthropology (BA)\n\nApplied Politics (MAP)\n\nApplied Water Science (BSc)\n\nArchaeology and Heritage Studies (BA)\n\nBA+MA in English, History or Political Science\n\nBiochemistry / Biotechnology (BSc)\n\nBiochemistry / Biotechnology (BSc) and Biotechnology Technician Diploma (with Conestoga College)\n\nBiological and Chemical Sciences (PhD)\n\nBiology (BA)\n\nBiology (BSc)\n\nBusiness Administration (BBA)\n\nBusiness Administration (BBA) and Computer Science (BCS) (with University of Waterloo)\n\nBusiness Administration (BBA) and Computer Science (BSc)\n\nBusiness Administration (BBA) and Financial Math (BA)\n\nBusiness Administration (BBA) and Math (BMath) (with University of Waterloo)\n\nBusiness Administration (Diploma)\n\nBusiness Administration (MBA)\n\nBusiness Economics (MABE)\n\nBusiness Technology Management (BBTM)\n\nChamber Music (Diploma)\n\nChemistry (BSc)\n\nChemistry (MSc)\n\nChristian Studies and Global Citizenship (BA)\n\nCommunication Studies (BA)\n\nCommunication Studies (MA)\n\nCommunity Health (BA)\n\nCommunity Music (MA)\n\nComputer Science (BA)\n\nComputer Science (BSc)\n\nComputing and Computer Electronics (BSc)\n\nCriminology (BA)\n\nCriminology (MA)\n\nCultural Analysis and Social Theory (MA)