(227, 'Galway Business School', NULL, 'Ireland', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Galbay.jpg', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Galway-Business-School.jpg', 'Ireland ', 'GCI House, Salthill, Galway, Ireland', 'The ICM- Institute of Commercial Management - is one of the most respected providers of professional business qualifications in Ireland and the UK.\nFETAC is the national awarding body for further education and training in Ireland\nFÁS Ireland''s National Training and Employment Authority.\nEDI is a leading accredited UK Awarding Body that offers over 370 vocational qualifications, both within the UK and internationally.', '• 50% in Bachelors Degree (Any stream)\n• IELTS 6.0\n• Lower than the above scores, student can opt for Pre-sessional English \n• Gap between 12th standard/Graduation till date should not be more than 2 year except in case of Masters where higher gap can be accepted based on experience.\n• Passport Copy\n• Updated Resume\n• 2 Recommendation Letters.\n', 'Private ', '900 EUR /Month ', 'POSTGRADUATE DIPLOMA IN MANAGEMENT\nBA HONOURS IN BUSINESS MANAGEMENT\nTOP UP BA HONOURS IN BUSINESS MANAGEMENTPostgraduate Diploma in Management BA in Marketing, Innovation, Sales & Technology (per year) BA in Business Management (Year 3) BA in Business Management (Year 2) BA in Business Management (Year 1) Top-up BA in Business Management Advanced Diploma in Business Advanced Diploma in Accounting & Finance Advanced Diploma in Marketing, Advertising & Public Relations Diploma in Business Diploma in Accounting & Finance Diploma in Marketing, Advertising & Public Relations Advanced Certificate in Sports Development', NULL, '4300', '1600', NULL, 'Sharing Base', '+353 91 529 000', NULL, '8,350 Euro per Year', 'March & September ', 'EUR 100 ', 'http://www.galwaybusinessschool.ie/', 'https://www.facebook.com/galwaybusinessschool.ie', NULL, NULL, 'https://linkedin.com/edu/school?id=153096&trk=tyah&trkInfo=clickedVertical%3Aschool%2CclickedEntityId%3A153096%2Cidx%3A2-1-5%2CtarId%3A1441123427609%2Ctas%3Agalway%20bus', NULL, NULL, NULL, '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Situated on Ireland’s west coast, Galway—the historic ‘City of the Tribes’—is a vibrant, lively city full of IT software specialists, students and tourists, creating an eclectic exchange of ideas and endless possibilities.\nIt is a great place to live, work and study.\nSituated on Ireland’s west coast, Galway—the historic ‘City of the Tribes’—is a vibrant, lively city full of IT software specialists, students and tourists, creating an eclectic exchange of ideas and endless possibilities.\nIt is a great place to live, work and study.\n1) Get Admission Without IELTS/TOFEL. \n\n2) Get Dual degree. MBA from University of Worcestor, UK and PG Diploma from Institute of Commercial Management. \n\n2) Low cost fee compare to UK education only 8,350 Euro where in UK fee start from 15,000 to 22,000 Euro per year.\n\n3) Student can work 20 Hrs per week part time.\n\n4) Programmes available In fields of Bussiness & Management. \n\n5) Study in Galyway for 1 year and study 1 more month in UK and get MBA degree from University  of Worcestor.\n\n6) All Programmes Starts in March & Sept 2014\n\n7) Paid Internships in Ireland\n\n8) Final Year graduate student can get admission directly in 3rd year in Top up Program and get Bachelor degree from Ireland. \n', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(228, 'Dublin Business School', 1975, 'Ireland', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/DBS-Logo.jpg', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Dublin-Business-School.jpg', 'Ireland ', '13-14 Aungier St, Dublin 2, Ireland', ' HETAC, HECA, Liverpool John Moores University', 'Entry requirement \nBachelors Degree - Minimum admission requirements: IELTS 6.0(with a minimum of 5.5 in each skill) with 55% in 12th grade. \nMasters Degree - Minimum admission requirements: IELTS 6.5(with a minimum of 6.0 in each skill) with 50% in Bachelors.', 'Private ', '900 EUR /Month ', 'Accounting and Finance\nArts\nBusiness and Management\nCounselling and Psychotherapy\nInformation Technology\nLaw\nMarketing and Event Management\nMedia and Journalism\nProfessional Accountancy\nPsychology and Social Science ', NULL, '9000', '2286', NULL, 'Sharing Base', '+353 1 417 7500', NULL, ' € 8400 - € 10,000 per year', 'March & September ', 'EUR 100 ', 'dbs.ie', NULL, NULL, 'https://www.google.co.in/url?sa=t&rct=j&q=&esrc=s&source=web&cd=31&cad=rja&uact=8&ved=0ahUKEwjDz8P_9NnOAhVEro8KHTvACpoQ9zAIwQEwHg&url=http%3A%2F%2Fplus.google.com%2F106029614477490385619&usg=AFQjCNFydPG0KO43aAgYuZ-xbq6MMur2tA&sig2=LXPbx4v6xZ-ZG0fN5y_', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Dublin Business School extends a warm Irish welcome to all international partners.DBS has over the last 36 years, established itself as a centre for international education excellence. The College has developed strategic links with a significant number of third level institutions in Europe, the US and Asia and has students currently from over 70 countries. Over the years the School has established partnership agreements with nearly 100 universities worldwide offering students the opportunity to attend for semester, dual degree and Masters Programmes and receive ECTS credits. Located in the heart of Dublin''s City centre, DBS aims to ensure that your students will have a rewarding and challenging experience as well as experiencing the culture and sights of a vibrant capital city. \n \nWhy DBS?\n\n \n1. City Centre Location: DBS is truly in the heart of Dublin city.\n2. Internationally Recognized Education Experience: Over the last 38 years DBS has established a considerable international reputation for the quality of its programmes. The College has created a unique learning environment with students from over 70 countries participating in its programmes. \n3. Ladder of Opportunity / Flexibility of Award Progression: Our certificate, degree and postgraduate programmes have been designed to allow students flexibility in their career choice. At DBS we have created a ''ladder of opportunity and progression'' for students who can create their own study pathway to achieve their individual educational goals. \n4. Student Centered Approach: In DBS we take a holistic view to college life. Academia should be integrated with a stimulating social scene. The work/study balance is something we regard at DBS as being important.\n \n', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(229, 'dublin city university', 1975, 'Ireland', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/DCU-Logo.png', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/dublin-city-university.jpg', 'Ireland ', 'Glanevin, Dublin 9, Ireland', ' AMBA\nESB Reutlingen\nEUA\nIUA\nUI', 'IELTS: Overall score of 6.5 or above, with no less than 6.0 in any one skill. DCU Business School additionally requires 6.5 in speaking and writing.\nTOEFL: Total Score of 92. DCU Business School additionally requires all section scores 21 or above.\nYour English language certificate must be awarded  within two years of the start date of your DCU programme.\nFull list of DCU English language entry requirements\nAcademic Entry Requirements', 'Private ', '900 EUR /Month ', 'Undergraduate Courses : Business Studies,  Global Business, Accounting and Finance, Economics, Politics and Law, Marketing Innovation and Technology, Aviation Management/ AM with Pilot Studies, Electronic and Computing Engineering (Majors in Electronic Hardware, Internet of Things/Embedded Systems, Digital Media/Communications Technology) Mechatronic Engineering, Mechanical and Manufacturing Engineering, Biomedical Engineering, Computer Applications, Enterprise Computing, Computational Problem Solving and Software Development, Contemporary Culture and Society, Communication Studies, Journalism, Multimedia, International Relations, Applied Language and Translation Studies, Civil Law, Economics, Politics and Law, Sport Science and Health, Athletic Therapy and Training, Physical Education with Biology, Physical Education with Mathematics, Science Education, Psychology, Health and Society                                                                        \n\n                                          \n\nPostgraduate Courses : MSc in Management (Business, Strategy, Digital Marketing), MSc International Management, MSc in Finance (Risk Mgmt. / Capital Markets / Energy Finance), Professional Diploma in Accounting, MSc in Electronic Commerce (Business), MEng in Telecommunications Engineering, MEng in Electronic Systems, MSc in Computer-Aided Mechanical and Manufacturing Engineering, MEng in Mechantronic Engineering, MSc in Electronic Commerce (Technical), MSc in Computing, MSc in Human Resource Management, MSc in Marketing, MSc in Humanitarian Logistics and Emergency Management, MA in International Relations, MA in Development, MA in International Security & Conflict, MA in Political Communication, MA in Film & Television Studies, MA in Journalism, MSc in Multimedia, MSc in Science Communication, MSc Biomedical Diagnostics, MSc in Bioprocess Engineering, MSc in Financial Mathematics\n\n \n\n', 'Chancellor Dr. Martin McAleese', '16000', '2000', NULL, 'Sharing Base', '353 1 700 5000', NULL, 'UG  Course fees  € 10,500 – 15,500\n\nLiving Cost -  € 7000 per year\n PG Course Fees  - € 12,500 – 16,000\n\n \n ', 'March & September ', 'ERU 100 ', ' http://www.dcu.ie/', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Dublin City University (abbreviated as DCU) (Irish: Ollscoil Chathair Bhaile Átha Cliath) is a university situated between Glasnevin, Santry, Ballymun and Whitehall on the Northside of Dublin in Ireland. Created as the National Institute for Higher Education, Dublin in 1975, it enrolled its first students in 1980 and was elevated to university status (along with the University of Limerick) in 1989 by statute.\nThe university currently has around 6,000 undergraduate students, over 600 research postgraduates, 1,800 taught postgraduate students and over 50,000 alumni.[2] In addition the university has around 1,200 online distance education students studying through DCU Connected.\nThe University has been designated as a Changemaker Campus by Ashoka U for its work in social innovation in higher education.\nThere were 440 academic staff in 2006. Notable members of the academic staff include former Taoiseach John Bruton and "thinking" Guru Edward De Bono. Bruton accepted a position as Adjunct Faculty Member in the School of Law and Government in early 2004 and De Bono accepted an adjunct Professorship in the university in mid-2005.\nThe founding president of the institution was Dr Danny O''Hare, who retired in 1999 after 22 years'' service. After a period of administration by an acting president (Professor Albert Pratt), Professor Ferdinand von Prondzynski, was appointed and continued as president for a full term, which ended in July 2010. He was succeeded by current president, Professor Brian MacCraith.', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
