 day by the establishment of Dublin City University.\nThe university is located along the River Shannon, on a 137.5 hectares (340 acres) campus comprising 46 hectares (110 acres) on the north bank and 91.5 hectares (226 acres) on the south bank, 5 km from Limerick city centre. The university has currently in excess of 11,000 full-time undergraduate students [5] and 1,500 part-time students.[citation needed] There are also over 800 research postgraduates and 1,300 taught postgraduate students[citation needed] at the university. The Co-operative Education (commonly called Co-Op) programme allocates all students with an 8-month work placement as part of their degree. This was the first such programmes in the state.\nProfessor Don Barry, a graduate of Yale University, is the current president of the university, having been appointed in 2007.[6]', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(240, 'American University of Antigua', 2004, 'Medical', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/American-University-of-Antigua-logo.png', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/American-University-of-Antigua-Back-ground.jpg', 'Jabberwock Beach Road, Antigua Guatemala, Antigua & Barbuda', NULL, 'Fully accredited off-shore US Medical SchoolAccredited by Caribbean Accreditation Authority for Education and Medicine and Other Professions (CAAM-HP)\nRecognized by the Medical Board of California\nApproved by the New York State Education Department\nAffiliated with Florida International University – Herbert Wertheim College of Medicine\n\n', 'US High School Diploma with a 3.0 GPA (or local equivalent)\nMinimum 550 TOEFL (paper-based) or 80 (computer) for non-native English speakers\nOfficial transcripts from all secondary and post-secondary schools attended\nPersonal statement\nCompleted application form\n', ' Private, for-profit', NULL, 'Pre Medical Cariculam\nAS in Health Sciences\nBS in Health SciencesBasic Sciences (2 years)\nClinical Sciences (2 years)\n', NULL, '1950', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1 212-661-8899', NULL, '$39,400 t- $1 09,200', 'Feb , Aug\n\n\n', '$100', ' www.auamed.org', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Wide choice of accommodation options \n400 seat outdoor Amphitheater for lectures, concerts and ceremonies\nBookstore\nCourtyard provides a landscaped gathering space with Wi-Fi coverage\nEducation Enhancement Department\nFood Court\nHealth Clinic\nAthletic Fields and Fitness Centre\nMile-long, white-sand beach\nFast-track alternative (Pre-Med) route to access medical school through partnership with American University of Antigua\nAccredited by the Accrediting Council of Independent Colleges and Schools, USA (ACICS)\nPrograms offered provide groundwork for degrees in medicine and health sciences\n', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
