ifying the payment of the part of the tuition fee, which exceeds the amount of the obtained state study, social or other grant; \ng) The applicants for the enrollment for an English-language program without taking the Unified National Examination shall be additionally required to present one of the language proficiency documents (if there is such), envisaged by Rules for Determination English Language Proficiency\nh) One of the following documents certifying the stay in a foreign country for two or more years (for foreign nationals, stateless persons or Georgian nationals, who acquired secondary of equivalent thereto education in a foreign country): \nh.a) A document, certifying the registration in a foreign country; \nh.b) A consulate registration document; \nh.c) Any other document, certifying the stay of the applicant in the foreign country in accordance with the law in force of the concerned.\n\n\nThe applicants for a Master’s program will be required to provide the University with the following documents: \na) A completed application form;\nb) A copy of an ID Card (for foreign nationals – a copy of every page of the passport/nationality identification document, for stateless persons – a copy of a residence certificate); \nc) One of the following qualification documents: \nc.a) A Bachelor Diploma; \nc.b) A copy of the respective higher education qualification document, issued by an authorized higher education institution of a foreign country;\nc.c) A copy of the document, certifying the acquisition of credits at a foreign higher education institution – for applicants, who study/studied and earned credits within the framework of a Master’s program at a foreign higher education institution duly authorized commensurate with the law in force of the country concerned. \nd) The applicants, who enrolled in a higher education institution commensurate with the Procedure of Enrolment without taking the Unified National Examination will be additionally required to present the following documents:\nd.a)  The copies of the qualification document acquired as a result of enrolment through the Procedure of Enrolment without taking the Unified National Examination – Diploma and Diploma Supplement; \nd.b) An act of the head of the higher education institution, certifying the enrolment of the applicant concerned for the first cycle of higher education at a higher education institution through the Procedure of Enrolment without taking the Unified National Examination;\ne) A copy of the document certifying military registration (only for Georgian nationals); \nf) A photo (3X4); \ng) The document certifying the payment of the tuition fee; \nh) The applicants for the enrollment for an English-language program without taking the Unified National Examination shall be additionally required to present one of the language proficiency documents (if there is such), envisaged by Rules for Determination English Language Proficiency;\ni) One of the following documents certifying the stay in a foreign country for two or more years (for foreign nationals, stateless persons or Georgian nationals, who acquired secondary of equivalent thereto education in a foreign country): \nh.a) A document, certifying the registration in a foreign country; \nh.b) A consulate registration document; \nh.c) Any other document, certifying the stay of the applicant in the foreign country in accordance with the law in force of the concerned\n\n\nPreconditions for the Enrolment for a Doctoral Program\na) A completed electronic application form;\nb) A copy of an ID Card (for foreign nationals – a copy of every page of the passport/nationality identification document, for stateless persons – a copy of a residence certificate); \nc) A qualification document (Master’s Diploma or equalized thereto qualification document);\nd) A photo (3X4); \ne) The document certifying the payment of the tuition fee; \nf) An international certificate certifying, at least B2 level proficiency in the English language of any other language proficiency document; \ng) Well-founded recommendation of the curator, which may contain some information about the education, working experience or earlier academic activities of the applicant. \n', NULL, NULL, '? General Medicine & Surgery (MBBS)\n? One Year Foundation Program\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '995 322 42 44 40', NULL, '$ 30 000 - $ 60 000 ', NULL, '$100', 'http://www.eng.newvision.ge/', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(246, 'Davao Medical School Foundation Inc', NULL, 'Medical', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Davao-Medical-School-Foundation-Inc-logo.jpg', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Davao-Medical-School-Foundation-Inc-Back-ground.jpg', 'Philippines', 'Bajada, Davao City, Davao del Sur, Philippines', NULL, '\n\nCompleted Application Form and Personal History Statement (can be downloaded in our website: www.dmsf.edu.ph)\n2.\nPhotocopy of Transcript of Records\n3.\nPhotocopy of National Medical Admission Test (NMAT) result\n4.\nLetter of Reference from two (2) former professors\n5.\nApplication Fee (non-refundable)\nB.\nSubmit above documents to:\nOffice of the Dean\nDavao Medical School Foundation\nMedical School Drive, Bajada, Davao City 8000\nPhilippines\nC.\n\n\n\nSubmitted documents in item A will be evaluated by the Office of the Dean, after which, the applicant is informed as to the status of his/her application. If applicant is qualified, the school will send to the applicant the following:\n1.\nNotice of Acceptance (NOA)*\n2.\nPersonal History Statement forms for the applicant to fill-up (6 copies)\n3.\n\nCertificate of Eligibility for Admission (CEA) form for the applicant to fill-up (not required for lateral entrants)\n*The Notice of Acceptance should not be construed as the actual enrollment.\nD.\n\n\n\nThe original documents listed in items A and C should be completed and mailed back to the Office of the Dean including the following documents duly authenticated by the Philippine Foreign Service Post (PFSP) in the country of origin:\n1.\nOfficial transcript of records and diploma;\n2.\n\n\n\nNotarized Affidavit of Support, including bank statements or notarized notice of grant for institutional scholars to cover applicant’s expenses for school dues, accommodation, subsistence and other incidental expenses;\n3.\n\nPhotocopy of passport pages where name, photo, birthday, birthplace appear;\n4.\n\nStudent’s Personal History Statement (6 copies) with 2 x 2 recently taken photograph;\n5.\n\nPolice Clearance issued by the National Police Authorities in the student’s country of origin or residence;\n6.\nBirth certificate;\n7.\nLetter of Recommendation from two former college professors;', NULL, NULL, 'The academic programs of Davao Medical School Foundation aims to develop the students with the knowledge, skills and potential that combine advanced work in the specific academic fields with courses in medical and dental, nursing and midwifery areas, thereby equipping students for professional employment in a variety of both private and public sector fields. This is inline with the DMSF''s objective of forming an integral man through educational enrichment guided by the Catholic faith.\n ', 'DR. JONATHAN A. ALEGRE, FPAFP', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '63 82 226 2344', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'https://www.google.co.in/url?sa=t&rct=j&q=&esrc=s&source=web&cd=23&cad=rja&uact=8&ved=0ahUKEwjG2ZyIiOHOAhUBqI8KHRYXBJ0Q9zAIoAEwFg&url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2FDavaoMedical&usg=AFQjCNEzTtYdc_-QA6z9HxgDmDYePjnRrg&sig2=HEkYkXqgKnmcdE6LFjXPNw&bvm=', 'https://www.google.co.in/url?sa=t&rct=j&q=&esrc=s&source=web&cd=23&cad=rja&uact=8&ved=0ahUKEwjG2ZyIiOHOAhUBqI8KHRYXBJ0Q9zAIngEwFg&url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.twitter.com%2Fdavaomedical&usg=AFQjCNHApicKnuMtf-X0jZcB7p8M8LKoqw&sig2=8dQEuYpQcJpY_C2urbWqSw&bvm=b', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'It brings great pleasure to invite everyone to visit our DMSFI website. The information you may get or pick from here comes with an opportunity that will somehow be useful as you get on with life, an individual - globally prepared and competitive.\n\nThe Davao Medical School Foundation, Inc. website offers information on various kinds of services that include excellent education for the following health professions: medicine, dentistry and nursing. The other related services are into: research, community development training center and extension works, general hospital services, training center, networking and foreign exchange programs.\nYour visit to our website means a lot to us and as you surf your way, may you find it interesting and informative, one that can inspire you to invite more of your friends to see our website.\nWe encourage you also to share your views, opinions and comments if you have, but in a way that is just, bear truth, and with great respect to human dignity.\nWELCOME & BE COUNTED AS A DMSFI WEBSITE SURFER!', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
