(249, 'CENTER FOR AMERICAN EDUCATION at TEXILA AMERICAN UNIVERSITY', NULL, 'Medical', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/CENTER-FOR-AMERICAN-EDUCATION-at-TEXILA-AMERICAN-UNIVERSITY-Logo.jpg', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/CENTER-FOR-AMERICAN-EDUCATION-at-TEXILA-AMERICAN-UNIVERSITY-Back-ground.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Texila American University – Center for American Education (TAU - CAE) & Broward College (BC) together offer a 2-year AA (Associate of Arts) program, which provides a pathway for transfer to most colleges and universities in USA, Canada, UK, Lebanon, UAE, Egypt and Japan.  \nAdvantages of TAU-CAE & BC Program  \nSince the duration of an American Degree is 4 years you can start the degree program right after your O’Levels. So by the time you are 19 or 20 years old you could have an American Bachelors degree in your hand, while your colleagues may still be struggling to enter a local university.  \nThe TAU-CAE offers 145 subjects at the degree level. So that students can complete half of almost any degree in Guyana - South America, before transferring to the United States and elsewhere to complete the remaining 2 years.  \nStudents are not restricted to transferring only to USA. After completing 2 years of study (61 Credits) at TAUCAE students can also transfer to other countries such as USA, Canada, UK, Lebanon, UAE, Egypt and Japan.  \nOver 2000 students completing this program at Broward College centers around the world have transferred to foreign universities mainly in the U.S. in fields including Pre-Medicine / Engineering / Business Studies / Computer Science / Psychology / Hospitality Management etc.  \nTexila American University & Broward College  \nTexila American University is located in, Georgetown, Guyana – South America and currently collaborates with Broward College - USA. Established in 1959 and located in Fort Lauderdale, Florida, Broward College is one of 28 public state colleges in the state of Florida, and serves over 65,000 students.    \nBroward College in Florida offers wide variety of programs including the four-year bachelor’s degrees ranging from Health Sciences to Business leading to different career opportunities in Allied Health, Business, Information Technology  \nThe intensive English Language Studies Program can prepare students whose first language is not English. TAU also offers a 8 weeks English training program for academic purposes to help Students who have not done their schooling in English or did not pass their TOEFL or IELTS.  \nTexila American University also offers full-time programs in Doctor of Medicine (MD), Doctor of Dental Surgery & Bachelor of Science in Nursing (BSN) Programs on its campus located in Georgetown, Guyana – South America.   ', 'Texila American University – Center for American Education (TAU - CAE) & Broward College (BC) togeth', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Broward College (BC) was established in 1959. It caters to over 65,000 full time and part-time students from all over the USA and other countries. BC offers academic as well as technical and occupational programs. Broward College is well-recognized for its dedication to international education programs. As such, BC has established formal linkages with several American college programs overseas. Currently, official BC relationships are maintained with the following institutions:  \n1. Texila American University (Guyana – South America)  2. Broward College Center for American Education (BCAE) Guayaquil (Ecuador) 3. American College of Higher Education (Sri Lanka) 4. Center for American Education (Singapore) 5. Center for International Education – National Management School (CIE-NMS) (India) 6. South Ocean College, Wuxi (China) 7. Institute for American Education – Vietnamese American Training College (IAE – VATC) (Vietnam) 8. Center for American Education at the Universidad San Ignacio de Loyola (CAE – USIL) (Peru)  \nBroward College is accredited by the Southern Association of Colleges and Schools’ Commission on Colleges to award Associate’s and Bachelor’s degrees. Texila American University is not accredited by the Commission on Colleges and the accreditation of Broward College does not extend to or include Texila American University or its students.  Although Broward College accepts certain course work in transfer toward a credential from Texila American University, or collaborates in other ways for generation of course credits or program credentials, other colleges and universities may or may not accept this work in transfer, even if it appears on a transcript from Broward College. This decision is made by the institution subsequently considering the possibility of accepting such credits.  \nBroward College will accept credits in transfer earned by students at Texila American University toward the Associate of Arts degree.  To receive a degree from Broward College, at least 25% of the coursework must be completed at a Broward College location, which includes SACS-approved international centers', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(250, 'UHSA ', 1982, 'Medical', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/UHSA-Logo.jpg', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/UHSA-back-ground.jpg', NULL, NULL, 'Since 1983, UHSA has been listed within the Avicenna Directory of Medical Schools, formerly the World Health Organization (WHO). UHSA is also recognized by the Education Commission for Foreign Medical Graduates (ECFMG), the Antigua & Barbuda National Accreditation Board (ABNAB), and listed within the International Medical Education Directory (IMED).\n\nThis recognition confers eligibility for the medical graduates of the university to take the United States Medical Licensing Examinations (USMLE) in the U.S. and is one of the requirements of the Professional and Linguistic Assessments Board (PLAB) in the U.K. Our listing in the International Medical Education Directory (IMED-FAIMER) also allows our students to take the Medical Council of Canada Qualifying Examination (MCCQE).  Nursing students are eligible to take the NCLEX examinations for licensure within the United States.\n\n', 'Applying is your first step to enrolling at UHSA and will immediately begin the admissions process. If you have any questions about the application or application process, please contact us. Before beginning the application, ensure that you have reviewed the Admission Requirements.\n\nApplication Steps\n\n·         Complete the application for admission\n\n·         Submit the required application fee online. You also have the option of submitting the payment via check or money order, to the address below.\n\n·         Upload your personal statement online in PDF/Word format or by emailing admissions@uhsa.edu.ag.\n\n·         Order official transcripts from all Universities/Colleges attended and have them mailed to the below address. You can e-mail unofficial transcripts pending your official transcripts.\n\n·         Request official letters of recommendation from individuals who can evaluate past academic and/or professional achievements. These letters must appear on original letterhead stationery and be sent directly from the individual giving the recommendation. Letters sent directly from the student will not be accepted.\n', NULL, NULL, 'M.D. Program\n\nThe M.D. Program at UHSA is a 4-Year semester based medical program that consists of Basic Sciences studies and Clinical Pathways leading to the Doctor of Medicine (M.D.) degree.  Each semester is 18-weeks, giving students a short break between their studies.  Students may apply for January and August start dates.\n\nThe first two years, semesters 1-4, are dedicated to completing the Basic Sciences at the serene UHSA campus on the beautiful island of Antigua.  We pride ourselves on ensuring that students receive personal attention.  Many of our expert faculty, who are recruited from U.S. medical schools and leading institutions around the world, live on-campus and are easily accessible by a students.\n\nUpon completion of the Basic Sciences, students spend the fifth semester (16-weeks) at Chicago’s Jackson Park Hospital completing the Integrated Review of the Basic Sciences.\n\nFollowing the fifth semester, students spend the final two years of the medical program completing the Clinical Sciences.\n\nUHSA’s M.D. curriculum is based upon the curriculum of U.S. medical schools and stresses problem-based methods of teaching within the classroom along with case studies.  Students begin to work with patients in the first semester at local clinics around the island where they are supervised by UHSA faculty as well as experienced practicing physicians and staff at the clinics and hospitals around the island.\nBSc leading to M.D. Program \n\nLondon Metropolitan University\n\nThe School of Medicine and London Metropolitan University offer a combined Biomedical Sciences pathway to M.D. Program that enables qualified individuals to complete requirements of both the B.S. in Biomedical Sciences and Doctor of Medicine (M.D.) degrees. The program enables students to be accepted to both institutions through a single joint admission process.\n\nThis program is only offered to full-time undergraduate Biomedical Sciences students at London Metropolitan University.  Students must display maturity, motivation, and intellectual capacity necessary for the combined program.\n\nAwarding of the M.D. degree is contingent upon successful completion of both the prescribed Biomedical Sciences undergraduate and Medical School curriculum requirements.\n\nUniversity of Wolverhampton \n\nThe University of Health Sciences Antigua has formed a partnership with the University of Wolverhampton in order to offer combined programs that lead to an internationally accredited Medical Doctorate upon successful completion. These pathways present an opportunity to study for a fantastic medical career whilst experiencing a new country located in the heart of the Caribbean. This program is only offered to full-time undergraduate Biomedical Sciences students at the University of Wolverhampton. \nCombined M.P.H./M.D. Program\n\nThe University of Health Sciences Antigua has partnered with Benedictine University, Illinois, which will allow UHSA medical students to pursue both an M.D. and Master’s Degree in Public Health (MPH).  The MPH segment of the combined program is delivered online and is available only to those already accepted to the UHSA Medical Doctor program.  The MD segment of the program follows the guidelines of the UHSA Medical Doctor Program.\n\nBenedictine’s accredited online MPH degree program compliments the UHSA Medical Doctor program by providing students with the essential tools to lead organizations, agencies and companies that deal with the vital issue of public health, such as improving access to health care and controlling infectious disease. Coursework in the online MPH program will prepare students to help improve lives and protect the health of individuals within communities through education, promotion of healthy lifestyles and research for disease and injury prevention.\n\nStudents will complete coursework in biostatistics, epidemiology, management, policy, behavioral and social aspects of public health, environmental health and biology provides a scientific and practical base for public health practice. Elective courses may be taken in a variety of areas such as health education, finance, law and information technology.\n\nEligible UHSA students pursuing the Benedictine MPH degree may apply for Title IV federal aid, which may be applied to the cost of Benedictine’s tuition as well as living expenses incurred while pursuing the degree from Benedictine.\n\n \n\nWhy Benedictine?\n\nBy earning your Master of Public Health online at Benedictine, UHSA students will receive all the benefits that Benedictine offers with its rich history spanning more than 120 years of academic excellence.\n\n·         Join an established program that is the second largest of its kind in Illinois\n\n·         Complete your coursework according to your own schedule with our fully online, interactive format\n\n·         Earn the same respected degree as students in the traditional, on-campus MPH program\n\n·         Get help from a full-time advisor when you need it\n\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Founded in 1982, the University of Health Sciences Antigua (UHSA) located in Dowhill, Piccadilly Antigua is an outstanding academic institution dedicated to educating exemplary physicians, nurses, postgraduates and researchers in accordance with the highest professional standards who will integrate clinical, biomedical and behavioral knowledge to promote the health and well-being of patients and communities.\n\nWe are committed to educating physicians and health care professionals who will address national and international challenges in medicine with an emphasis on primary care and be known for excellence in practice, service, compassion, collegiality and scientific curiosity while demonstrating sensitivity to the diverse cultural environments in which medical care is delivered.\n\nA Personalized Approach to Medical Education\n\nOur curriculum has been designed taking into consideration, the need for knowledge of today’s physicians. Due to the solid foundation of the courses taught, our students are very successful during the clinical portion of the UHSA medical program. This is an important factor in successfully passing the required licensing examinations.\n\nSince 1982, UHSA has graduated students from over 21 countries and 45 states within the U.S. Our students are represented in just about every specialty including, surgery, obstetrics and gynecology, internal medicine, and pediatrics. UHSA students have also gone on to prominent positions such as Heads of Hospitals, Department heads, Faculty, Chief residents, popular lecturers, etc.\n\nAt UHSA, you are more than just a number, you’re family. You will not find yourself in a classroom with hundreds of other students. One of the benefits of attending a smaller institution, such as UHSA, is the opportunity to experience a personalized education. You will be welcomed by faculty who live on campus, know your name, and who support you even outside of the classroom.\n\nSmaller class size also means that there is no need to compete for clinical placements. With an extensive list of US Hospital Affiliations, our students are treated with the highest priority when it comes to hospital placement. After all, what is the reason for attending medical school if you are unable to gain hospital experience?\n', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(260, 'AUT University', 2000, 'New Zealand', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/AUT-University-2015.jpg', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/AUT.jpg', ' Auckland , New Zealand', ' 55 Wellesley St E, Auckland 1010, New Zealand', NULL, 'Doctorate\n\n6.5 overall with 7 in Writing and all other bands 6.0 or higher\n\nPostgraduate Programmes (Master''s, Postgraduate Diplomas, Postgraduate Certificates and Bachelor with Honours)\n\n6.5 overall with all bands 6 or higher\n\nGraduate Diplomas and Certificates and Conjoint Degrees\n6.5 overall with all bands 6 or higher\n\nBachelor''s Degree\n\n6 overall with all bands 5.5 or higher\n\nDiplomas\n\nDepending on particular diploma, either 6 overall with all bands 5.5. or higher, or 5.5 overall with all bands 5 or higher (see the Academic calendar for further information)\n\nCertificates\n\n5.5 overall with all bands 5 or higher\n', 'Public', '$10000', 'http://www.aut.ac.nz/s/search.html?query_phrase=&collection=aut-ac-nz-meta&form=courses&sitetheme=red&meta_M_orsand=%5BUndergraduate+Postgraduate+Certificates+Diplomas+Short+Courses%5D&f.Course+Type%7CM=Undergraduate&f.Course+Type%7CM=Postgraduate&f.Course+Type%7CM=Certificates+and+Diplomas&f.Course+Type%7CM=Short+Courses', NULL, '27500', NULL, NULL, 'On Campus/Off Campus', NULL, 'admission@studymetro.com', 'Programme Duration Intake Tuition fees $NZ\nCertificates (6 Months)\nCertificate in Business 6 Months Feb/July 15,330 (full tuition fee)\nCertificate in ', '$150', NULL, 'http://www.aut.ac.nz/', 'https://www.facebook.com/autuni', 'https://twitter.com/autuni', NULL, 'https://www.linkedin.com/edu/school?id=15502', 'https://www.instagram.com/autuni/', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/AUTUniversity', NULL, '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, 'AUT University', 'Data and statistics about Auckland University of Technology (AUT) and its students and graduates, qualifications, and teaching and research facilities. Notes about AUT''s background and establishment as a university.\n\nAUT''s background\n\nAUT Crest\n\nWe’re New Zealand’s newest university but our history in industry-relevant education is over 110 years old. We perform our teaching, research and other duties as defined under the Education Act (1989).\n\nEstablished as a university\n\nIn 2000, the governor general, by order in council, established the Auckland University of Tec\n\nhnology as one of the universities in New Zealand. AUT is the youngest of the eight New Zealand universities and the only one to be established since the 1960s.', 'AUT is a contemporary New Zealand university focused on providing exceptional student opportunities and learning experiences, and graduate success in a context stimulated by impactful research and industry connectivity.\n\nMore than 26,000 students are enrolled at AUT in undergraduate and postgraduate programmes, studying at one of our three campuses. We have consistently been a leader in undergraduate and postgraduate enrolment growth of both New Zealand and international students across a wide range of professional disciplines, and as a result we are now the second largest university in New Zealand.', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
