(300, 'Liverpool John Moores University', 1823, 'UK', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/john-moores.jpg', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/john-moores1.jpg', ' Liverpool, United Kingdom', '70 Mount Pleasant, Liverpool L3 5UA, United Kingdom', NULL, 'IELTS\n6.0 (Min 5.5 in each component)\n\nPearson\n50-57\n\n', 'Public', '£10,000', 'https://www.ljmu.ac.uk/study/courses', NULL, '20365', NULL, NULL, 'On Campus /Off Campus', '44 151 231 2121', 'admission@studymetro.com', '£12,360', NULL, NULL, 'https://www.ljmu.ac.uk/', 'https://www.facebook.com/liverpooljohnmooresuniversity', 'https://twitter.com/LJMU', NULL, 'https://www.linkedin.com/edu/liverpool-john-moores-university-12607', NULL, 'https://www.youtube.com/user/LJMUTV', NULL, '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, 'Liverpool John Moores University', 'In 1823 a small institution was founded that was to revolutionise education in Liverpool and provide opportunities for the working people of the city.\nThe Liverpool Mechanics Institute was founded by people of power and influence who recognised the transformative effects of education and the impact that learning and aspiration could have on individuals, communities and society.  It was the first such institution to be founded in England.  \n\nThis small, pioneering movement was followed by the establishment of the Liverpool Institute and School of Art and the Liverpool Nautical College, and in 1900 Irene Mabel Marsh opened the IM Marsh campus. These organisations together laid the foundations for Liverpool John Moores University, an institution that has grown and flourished and continues to provide opportunities for all.', 'One University\nWe are an ambitious and forward thinking institution that challenges convention and believes passionately in the concept of ‘One University’ – a community working together to achieve common student-centered objectives within a clear strategy.\nOur Vision\nTo be recognised as a modern civic university delivering solutions to the challenges of the 21st century.\n\nOur Mission\nCreating a community for learning and knowledge\n\nOur mission is to create and sustain a vibrant community for learning and knowledge where staff and students work together in an active and supportive partnership; providing opportunities to enrich our students, partners and the wider society through education, training, research, scholarship and knowledge transfer.', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(301, 'LONDON COLLEGE OF INTERNATIONAL BUSINESS STUDIES', NULL, 'UK', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/London-College-Of-business-studies.jpg', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/London-College-Of-business-studies1.jpg', 'London , United Kingdom', 'Dock Offices, Surrey Quays Rd, London SE16 2XU, United Kingdom', NULL, 'IELTS\n6.0 (Min 5.5 in each component)', 'Public', '£10,000', 'Certificate in Strategic Management and Leadership\nExtended Diploma in Strategic Management & Leadership\nMBA Top-Up\nBBA Top-Up\n\nHND Diploma in Business (Management)\nHND Diploma in Business (Marketing)\nHND Diploma in Business (Human Resources)\nHND Diploma in Business (Accounting)\nHND Diploma in Business (Public Relations)\nHND Diploma in Business (Hospitality)\nHND Diploma in Business (Travel & Tourism)\nHND Diploma in Business (Sport & Leisure Management)\n\n\n\nHNC Certificate in Business (Management)\nHNC Certificate in Business (Marketing)\nHNC Certificate in Business (Human Resources)\nHNC Certificate in Business (Accounting)\nHNC Certificate in Business (Public Relations)\nHNC Certificate in Business (Hospitality)\nHNC Certificate in Business (Travel & Tourism)\nHNC Certificate in Business (Sport & Leisure Management)\n\n\nCertificate/Diploma in Business Administration\nCertificate/Diploma in Management\nCertificate/Diploma in Marketing\nCertificate/Diploma in Human Resources\nCertificate/Diploma in Accounting\nCertificate/Diploma in Public Relations\nCertificate/Diploma in Hospitality\nCertificate/Diploma in Travel & Tourism\nCertificate/Diploma in Sport & Leisure Management\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'On Campus /Off Campus', NULL, 'admission@studymetro.com', '£7,550 or £9,000 (including Internship)', NULL, NULL, 'http://www.lcibs.org/', 'https://www.facebook.com/LCIBS', 'https://twitter.com/LCIBS', NULL, 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/london-college-of-international-business-studies', NULL, 'https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC3EwvgIRdVfnW8HeTc8mZVg', NULL, '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null," "]', NULL, 'LONDON COLLEGE OF INTERNATIONAL BUSINESS STUDIES', '\nLCIBS Beginnings\nIn 1994, LCIBS moved to 14 Southampton Place, an attractive Grade II listed Georgian building in London’s Bloomsbury. It’s thought that this part of London was originally designed by the major 18th century architect Henry Flitcroft (1697-1769), who was responsible for several town houses in the Bloomsbury area.', 'Today, over 140 years from our beginnings, we continue to adapt to real world business demands and the needs of students who require the best skills to succeed in the global market place.\n\nIn 2012, we became qualified to deliver higher education to our students through our partnership with Pearson Edexcel focusing on HNC/D and the Level 7 award, the Extended Diploma in Strategic Management and Leadership (EDSML).\n\nIn 2014, our first higher education students graduated. We also became part of Linden Education Partners, a worldwide group specialising in education while our partnership with UBIS now allows students to top-up their BAs and MBAs.\n\nIn 2015 the college moved to larger premises at Canada Water providing the foundations for a new and exiting direction in our long history.', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(302, 'London School of Business and Management', NULL, 'UK', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/london-school-of-business-and-management-logo.jpg', 'About the University\nThe University of Sussex is a leading higher education and research institution near Brighton, in the south of England. Sussex was the first of the new wave of UK universities founded in the 1960s, receiving its Royal Charter in ', ' London, United Kingdom', 'Dilke House, 1 Malet St, London WC1E 7JN, United Kingdom', NULL, 'Undergraduate – IELTS 6.0 overall, with all components 5.5 or above\nMBA and MSc Management – IELTS 6.5 overall, with all components 5.5 or above\nLLM – IELTS 6.5 overall, with all components 6.0 or above\n', 'Public', '£10,000', 'Undergraduate Courses\nBusiness\nLaw\nAccounting\nPostgraduate Courses\nBusiness\nLaw', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'On Campus /Off Campus', '44 20 7078 8840', 'admission@studymetro.com', '£10,000 ', NULL, NULL, 'http://www.lsbm.ac.uk/', 'https://www.facebook.com/1LSBM/', 'https://twitter.com/lsbm', 'http://uk.linkedin.com/company/london-school-of-business-and-management', NULL, NULL, 'https://www.youtube.com/user/LondonBusinessSchool', NULL, '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, 'London School of Business and Management', 'The London School of Business and Management is a vibrant and contemporary learning community that seeks to meet the needs of all our students by offering networking opportunities and a uniquely international environment. We are proud of our diverse and vibrant student body.\n', 'We offer a range of valuable services to accommodate the needs of our students and to help them adjust to London’s rich and diverse way of life, including:\nan excellent location in the heart of London’s academic area of Bloomsbury, full of vibrant student life and close to numerous libraries, museums and centres of research, not to mention our proximity to the hub of business and finance that is the City of London.\na very welcoming environment of inclusivity and diversity\nhighly competitive fees; amongst the best value provision in the UK\ntransferability of credit accumulated on other courses undertaken at selected educational institutions within the UK and around the world\nopportunities to gain valuable professional experience through the work placement module on both undergraduate and postgraduate courses\nhelp and support with visa applications for non-EU students\nhelp and support in finding suitable and affordable accommodation\nextra English language support classes if required\nthe services of our faculty members, many of whom hold a PhD or are working towards their doctorate – our lecturers also have practice-based experience, providing our students with a ‘real-world’ dimension to their academic studies\nsmall class sizes allowing lecturers to provide excellent individual support in a collaborative learning context', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(303, 'Met Film School', 2003, 'UK', 'http://www.htir.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/MET_FILM_WHTE.jpg', 'https://www.instagram.com/sussexuni/', ' London, United Kingdom', 'Bldg E Ealing Studios, Ealing Green, London W5 5EP, United Kingdom', NULL, 'IELTS\n6.0 (Min 5.5 in each component)', 'Public', '£10,000', '2-YEAR DEGREE\nBA (HONS) PRACTICAL FILMMAKING\n3-YEAR DEGREE\nBA (HONS) PRACTICAL FILMMAKING\nDIPLOMA OF HIGHER EDUCATION\nPRACTICAL FILMMAKING DIPLOMA (DIP HE)\nCERTIFICATE OF HIGHER EDUCATION\nCERTIFICATE IN PRACTICAL FILMMAKING COURSE\nMA\nDIRECTING\nMA\nPRODUCING\nMA\nCINEMATOGRAPHY\nMA\nSCREENWRITING\nMA\nPOSTPRODUCTION\nMA\nDOCUMENTARY & FACTUALSIX-MONTH\nPRACTICAL FILMMAKING\nSIX-MONTH\nPOSTPRODUCTION\nSIX-MONTH\nDIGITAL ANIMATION & VFX  FILMMAKING\nFROM STORY TO SCREEN IN EIGHT WEEKS\nDOCUMENTARY\nDOCUMENTARY FILMMAKING\nFILMMAKING\nFOUR-WEEK FILMMAKING\nEDITING & POSTPRODUCTION\nTHREE-WEEK EDITING\nACTING\nACTING FOR FILM LEVEL 1\nACTING\nACTING FOR FILM LEVEL 2\nCINEMATOGRAPHY\nINTRODUCTION TO CINEMATOGRAPHY\nPOSTPRODUCTION\nSIX-MONTH DIGITAL ANIMATION & VFX\nFILMMAKING\nSIX-MONTH PRACTICAL FILMMAKING\nPOSTPRODUCTION\nSIX-MONTH POSTPRODUCTION', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'On Campus /Off Campus', NULL, 'admission@studymetro.com', '£17,500', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'https://www.facebook.com/MetFilmSchool', 'https://twitter.com/MetFilmSchool', NULL, 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/met-film-school?trk=ppro_cprof', NULL, 'https://www.youtube.com/c/metfilmschool', NULL, '[null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null]', NULL, 'Met Film School', 'Review by the Quality Assurance Agency for Higher Education\n\nFrom the evidence provided in the annual return and at the monitoring visit, the review team concluded that Met Film School has made commendable progress with implementing the action plan from the September 2014:\n\nThe School continues to operate as one of three interconnected businesses, along with a commercial film production company and a post-production company, both of which provide opportunities for work placements and graduate employment. It continues to develop its curriculum further by promoting and expanding current industry links and expertise, and award-winning industry professionals continue to teach on the programmes.\nThe School continues to provide and expand the variety of employment opportunities for students and to monitor graduate employment statistics. Met Film School Graduate Opportunities (Met GO) is now firmly embedded within the School’s ethos.\nThe School continues to enhance its rigorous approach to admissions and the innovative induction process.', 'The BA (Hons) Practical Filmmaking Programme has been awarded a Creative Skillset Tick. This award is a mark of quality indicating programmes best suited to prepare students for a career in the creative industries.\nTo gain the Creative Skillset Tick, programmes need to undergo a rigorous assessment process conducted by experts in the creative industries. They only give the Tick to programmes with the strongest links with industry. This ensures that the courses keep up the rapid pace of creative change, and students’ benefit from using the latest technologies an working with industry throughout their studies.', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
